{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1013", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The slow food movement originated in Italy over 30 years ago to promote local food culture and preserve traditional cuisine.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement was founded by Carlo Petrini in 1986 in reaction to the opening of a McDonald's in Rome's Piazza di Spagna.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0, "e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 0.5}}, {"text": "The slow food spirit is based on \"Good, clean and fair\" principles.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement aims to preserve local food cultures and promote sustainable tourism.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0, "e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 0.5}}, {"text": "The International Slow Food Headquarters, located in Italy, has projects like Ark of Taste and Slow Food Presidia that preserve traditional food and cooking methods.", "citations": {"573bbdbd-ccb5-417f-82b3-117a2073ed1c_97571398": 1.0, "ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 0.5}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has been promoted in Taitung, Taiwan for over 10 years with a festival held every spring and autumn.", "citations": {"21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534": 1.0, "573bbdbd-ccb5-417f-82b3-117a2073ed1c_97571398": 0.5, "89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 0.25, "bef51873-d3bd-4cc6-b635-f7eb2515325e_755701371": 0.125}}, {"text": "The festival features traditional ingredients and contemporary stories, winning Japan's Good Design Award.", "citations": {"21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534": 1.0, "89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 0.5, "bef51873-d3bd-4cc6-b635-f7eb2515325e_755701371": 0.25}}, {"text": "The movement is also practiced in countries including India, Malaysia, and the Philippines.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0, "573bbdbd-ccb5-417f-82b3-117a2073ed1c_97571398": 0.5, "b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612": 0.25}}, {"text": "Proponents of the slow food movement include Carlo Petrini, Haeyoung Kim, and the Hualien County Government in Taiwan.", "citations": {"e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 1.0, "e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959": 0.5}}, {"text": "One can sample the best slow food cuisine at the Taitung Slow Food Festival in Taiwan or the International Slow Food Headquarters in Italy.", "citations": {"21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534": 1.0, "573bbdbd-ccb5-417f-82b3-117a2073ed1c_97571398": 0.5, "89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 0.25, "bef51873-d3bd-4cc6-b635-f7eb2515325e_755701371": 0.125}}, {"text": "The movement has a presence in other countries, with global events like Terra Madre and international forums.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0, "ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 0.5}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has expanded to slow living, design, and travel, focusing on sustainability and local ingredients.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0, "e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 0.5, "e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959": 0.25}}, {"text": "The movement has over 100,000 global members and a global presence with proponents and events around the world.", "citations": {"e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 1.0, "7c2a1fe5-6d77-43d3-b615-45dfa7772754_981252650": 0.5}}, {"text": "However, the movement also risks bowlification, which strips traditional cuisines of their authenticity through gentrification.", "citations": {"b2314b49-43dc-438c-adbb-acc4a4013289_580458455": 1.0}}, {"text": "Preserving regional dishes and promoting local food cultures is crucial, as is recognizing the importance of cultural exchange, and can bring economic benefits to local communities.", "citations": {"9d61616b-7b21-4857-a3b9-6290ccf722ea_709642148": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement promotes local food culture, preserves traditional cuisine, and supports sustainable agriculture, emphasizing authenticity and cultural exchange.", "citations": {"ddc58739-3eff-43d5-908b-9e13da60c3f6_879804265": 1.0}}], "references": ["89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945", "21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534", "b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612", "ddc58739-3eff-43d5-908b-9e13da60c3f6_879804265", "b2314b49-43dc-438c-adbb-acc4a4013289_580458455", "96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237", "bef51873-d3bd-4cc6-b635-f7eb2515325e_755701371", "e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959", "7c2a1fe5-6d77-43d3-b615-45dfa7772754_981252650", "573bbdbd-ccb5-417f-82b3-117a2073ed1c_97571398", "ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831", "9d61616b-7b21-4857-a3b9-6290ccf722ea_709642148", "347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333", "e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1014", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The slow food movement originated in Italy over 30 years ago, with a focus on promoting \"Good quality, clean and fair\" food.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement was started by Carlo Petrini in the 1980s as a reaction to fast food, specifically after McDonald's opened in Rome's heart.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0}}, {"text": "Carlo Petrini formed Slow Food to defend regional food traditions.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement gained supporters in over 150 countries and has been popular for over 30 years.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement promotes \"Good quality, clean and fair\" food and focuses on community power and cultural inheritance.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement aims to preserve traditional food culture and respects seasonality, minimizing environmental impact.", "citations": {"96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement has projects like Ark of Taste and Slow Food Presidia, which work to preserve traditional food and cuisine.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}, {"text": "Terra Madre is the Slow Food Global Conference, which brings together slow food activists from around the world.", "citations": {"21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534": 1.0}}, {"text": "The International Slow Food Headquarters is located in Italy, and the movement has representatives from various countries.", "citations": {"b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has spread worldwide, with a presence in countries like the Philippines, India, and Malaysia.", "citations": {"b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement promotes cultural exchange and learning, and slow food festivals are organized to showcase local cuisine.", "citations": {"b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612": 1.0}}, {"text": "One of the key events in the slow food movement is the Slow Food Festival, which is held annually in various locations, including Taitung, Taiwan.", "citations": {"89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 1.0}}, {"text": "Taitung Slow Food Festival features local terroir ingredients and food culture, and encourages the use of local ingredients in dishes.", "citations": {"89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 1.0}}, {"text": "The festival promotes a slow lifestyle and economy, and has won Japan's Good Design Award.", "citations": {"89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement also explores sustainable economic models and promotes fair and pure fishing methods through the Slow Fish movement.", "citations": {"ceff1569-8569-4274-b28c-d353482f1edb_384120809": 1.0}}, {"text": "To sample the best slow food cuisine, one can attend the Taitung Slow Food Festival or visit other locations that promote slow food, such as Hualien County in Taiwan.", "citations": {"ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has been promoted in various countries, including Taiwan, where the Taitung County Government has organized the slow food festival for over 10 years.", "citations": {"21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534": 1.0}}, {"text": "Current proponents of the slow food movement include Chef Kim Hai-ying, who founded the Korean Slow Food Organization.", "citations": {"e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement emphasizes sustainability and local ingredients, and has international certification programs.", "citations": {"e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some notable slow food restaurants in Taitung include Sinasera 24, Ibu, and Podium, which offer high-quality cuisine and unique dining experiences.", "citations": {"3fc69ada-2a1c-4fd5-8170-51f5cd3e823c_326356796": 1.0, "6cb46644-a626-4ca2-b752-f5d69a3cfc82_396781945": 0.5}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has also been promoted through events such as the Terra Madre Salone del Gusto, a global slow food conference.", "citations": {"ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 1.0}}, {"text": "The conference brings together slow food activists and representatives from around the world to discuss environment, climate, and public health.", "citations": {"ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 1.0}}, {"text": "Hualien County in Taiwan is another location that promotes slow food, with a focus on \"high-quality\", \"clean\", and \"fair\" principles.", "citations": {"ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 1.0}}, {"text": "The county hosts the Hualien International Slow Food Forum, which is held every two years.", "citations": {"ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831": 1.0}}, {"text": "The slow food movement has also been recognized by the Philippine government, which has closed tourist destinations such as Boracay due to the negative impact of tourism.", "citations": {"e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 1.0}}, {"text": "The movement encourages slow travel, which reduces mobility by plane and car, promoting sustainable tourism.", "citations": {"e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 1.0}}, {"text": "Slow travel helps preserve the environment and local cultures, and can be done with any time frame or budget, focusing on experience over speed.", "citations": {"e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the slow food movement is a global phenomenon that promotes local food cultures and traditional cuisines, while also supporting sustainable agriculture and fair food systems.", "citations": {"347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333": 1.0}}], "references": ["e67a5795-5982-45ea-b316-ae40e65f5aa4_478826959", "e5453a54-a53d-46c1-88ec-cb93130fa116_485767238", "3fc69ada-2a1c-4fd5-8170-51f5cd3e823c_326356796", "96da40f6-f654-43da-a3f7-d19d9c31ede9_78339237", "b702106c-5025-4436-a5d8-8cb8153a683a_482923612", "ceff1569-8569-4274-b28c-d353482f1edb_384120809", "ba5e7a01-a860-4e26-a47c-0e52b3c682e6_174285831", "21597006-6a4b-4e4d-bdb3-16063020492e_526063534", "347aa98a-ba79-4341-963b-fe558f633c81_611052333", "89e87dc2-272d-4055-8419-f253560719f7_771613945", "6cb46644-a626-4ca2-b752-f5d69a3cfc82_396781945"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1015", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The flat Earth theory is a pseudoscientific idea that has been present in some religions and spread through conspiracy theories in the US and Europe.", "citations": {"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167": 1.0}}, {"text": "Flat Earth societies exist in various countries, including the UK, where they are found in universities like York, Nottingham Trent, and Cambridge.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569": 1.0}}, {"text": "In the UK, flat Earth theory is considered pseudoscientific, often depicted as a disk with a 46-meter ice wall.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Romanian Intelligence Agency is aware of a small number of flat Earth theory followers in Romania.", "citations": {"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ashraf al-Kaali, a Tunisian media professional, promotes flat Earth theory on the channel \"Ninth\".", "citations": {"7614d155-5beb-49f4-b13a-4f2675a1d6c8_866557951": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tsargrad promotes flat Earth theory in Russia, with 5816 followers.", "citations": {"ca40ec82-78d0-48df-a54a-d1734fe3a0b3_53647378": 1.0}}, {"text": "Kyrie Irving, a professional basketball player, and Yuri Loza, among other celebrities, have endorsed the flat Earth theory, questioning space and space travel.", "citations": {"23318c83-eda0-48f0-a034-06b1ed01ea90_1005393558": 1.0}}, {"text": "Flat earthers argue that the earth is fixed and the sun revolves around it, citing misinterpreted religious texts, such as the Quran's description of the sun's movement towards a resting place.", "citations": {"1794e4e9-24d7-4c79-be00-2fedf0c6b128_30859492": 1.0}}, {"text": "The resurgence of flat Earth beliefs is due to misinformation on social media and a lack of scientific literacy.", "citations": {"a5850adf-60e5-4749-981d-9a7d886f3ebf_113485172": 1.0}}, {"text": "Social media has helped spread the flat Earth theory by connecting like-minded individuals and allowing them to promote their beliefs.", "citations": {"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167": 1.0}}, {"text": "People who believe in a flat Earth tend to distrust scientists and engage more with social media and conspiracy theories, with millennials and Gen Z being more likely to believe in such theories due to high social media engagement.", "citations": {"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675": 1.0}}, {"text": "Believing in conspiracy theories, such as flat Earth, can harm mental health, and education and critical thinking skills help children judge true or false information and avoid misinformation harm.", "citations": {"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675": 1.0}}, {"text": "To mitigate the risks of a child being influenced by false information, parents should maintain good communication with them, monitor their internet time, and teach critical thinking.", "citations": {"0bccd2ff-59da-4f33-8440-d01ae62047f8_910576184": 1.0}}, {"text": "Teaching critical thinking is essential in today's information age to recognize unreliable information and sources.", "citations": {"0e11d42f-a5b1-4bbb-b585-84e3274a7239_534772390": 1.0}}, {"text": "Parents, educators, and tech companies must collaborate to protect children from misinformation and promote media literacy.", "citations": {"f41a3548-6dfb-492a-bad1-b087bafba0ab_1049348392": 1.0}}], "references": ["1794e4e9-24d7-4c79-be00-2fedf0c6b128_30859492", "6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320", "4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569", "ca40ec82-78d0-48df-a54a-d1734fe3a0b3_53647378", "23318c83-eda0-48f0-a034-06b1ed01ea90_1005393558", "23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675", "7614d155-5beb-49f4-b13a-4f2675a1d6c8_866557951", "a5850adf-60e5-4749-981d-9a7d886f3ebf_113485172", "f41a3548-6dfb-492a-bad1-b087bafba0ab_1049348392", "f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167", "0e11d42f-a5b1-4bbb-b585-84e3274a7239_534772390", "0bccd2ff-59da-4f33-8440-d01ae62047f8_910576184"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1016", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The contemporary Internet-era flat Earth believers have gained significant attention in recent years, with various organizations and public figures promoting this idea, including Together for the Netherlands, which organized a demonstration in Amsterdam.", "citations": {"033e7078-07c7-4ddd-b9e5-a28f34f6a60b_219816380": 1.0}}, {"text": "In the United Kingdom, flat Earth societies exist in British universities, such as York, Nottingham Trent, and Cambridge, which has led to criticism from renowned figures like Richard Dawkins.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some public figures, such as Kyrie Irving, a celebrity athlete, have endorsed flat Earth beliefs, ignoring science and facts, and have been criticized by other public figures for their views.", "citations": {"23318c83-eda0-48f0-a034-06b1ed01ea90_1005393558": 1.0}}, {"text": "The flat Earth theory has also spread to the Arab world, often combined with conspiracy theories, and has been promoted by various media channels, including videos and documentaries.", "citations": {"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167": 1.0}}, {"text": "The reasons for the resurgence of flat Earth theory in the modern world are not fully understood, but may be related to the spread of misinformation on social media and the decline of trust in institutions.", "citations": {"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675": 1.0}}, {"text": "The characteristics of people who are most likely to subscribe to flat Earth beliefs include a tendency towards conspiratorial thinking, overconfidence, and cognitive biases, as well as certain personality traits and demographic factors.", "citations": {"b2ccce63-b582-410c-aeb7-c5b78b82effc_16861991": 1.0}}, {"text": "Exposure to conspiracy theories, such as the flat Earth belief, can harm critical thinking skills in teenagers, and being friends with someone who holds flat Earth beliefs may hinder this development.", "citations": {"0e11d42f-a5b1-4bbb-b585-84e3274a7239_534772390": 1.0}}, {"text": "To effectively communicate with their child about the concerns of being friends with someone who holds unconventional or misinformation-based beliefs, parents should initiate conversations with kids about concerns and create a comfortable space for them to ask questions.", "citations": {"3ba8171a-5025-4b71-b03e-3be6260dfef4_336902935": 1.0}}, {"text": "Parents should also maintain good communication with their children to overcome social pressures and get to know their child's friends to understand the influences their child is exposed to.", "citations": {"0bccd2ff-59da-4f33-8440-d01ae62047f8_910576184": 1.0}}, {"text": "The potential long-term effects of flat Earth beliefs on teenagers' mental health and well-being are likely to be negative, and may include increased stress, anxiety, and depression, as well as a lack of trust in credible sources of information.", "citations": {"09d92795-1631-4e65-bac3-c5d09870b930_588168351": 1.0}}, {"text": "Educational institutions and policymakers have a crucial role to play in promoting critical thinking skills and media literacy, and in protecting teenagers from the negative effects of misinformation.", "citations": {"06cf8da7-ed0e-4e5d-80c5-4fda071c7518_519693460": 1.0}}, {"text": "Critical thinking is developed through evaluating information reliability, which is essential in addressing concerns about flat Earth beliefs among teenagers, and teaching critical thinking helps combat misinformation.", "citations": {"1898ccb2-a289-4b8c-b712-f9c1a8916fb4_123956340": 1.0}}, {"text": "Media literacy education can help prevent mental health problems and cyberbullying, and it is being mandated in some states, such as California, for K-12 students.", "citations": {"53fa52a4-5a1f-4e90-a8cf-c1cb7d5ca335_223558017": 1.0}}, {"text": "The National Institute for Astronomical Research confirms that Earth is spherical and warns against publishing conspiracy theories and pseudoscience, and astronomy research supports Earth's spherical shape since ancient times.", "citations": {"af07cd35-8c56-40f2-a245-85d82c52d4b9_576268285": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, despite the overwhelming evidence, flat Earth societies exist at British universities like York and Cambridge, and some public figures like Richard Dawkins criticize universities for tolerating flat Earth ideas.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569": 1.0}}, {"text": "Children start believing unproven conspiracy theories at age 14, and over 80% of middle school students mistake sponsored ads for news, making them vulnerable to misinformation.", "citations": {"f0932c14-bf26-4a29-a8e3-cbacb4a1a279_599324161": 1.0}}, {"text": "The algorithms used by social media platforms like YouTube play a critical role in spreading false information, and collective action is necessary to protect children from misinformation.", "citations": {"f0932c14-bf26-4a29-a8e3-cbacb4a1a279_599324161": 1.0}}, {"text": "Education is important to help children judge true or false information, and critical thinking skills are necessary to combat false information.", "citations": {"f0932c14-bf26-4a29-a8e3-cbacb4a1a279_599324161": 1.0}}, {"text": "Parents and educators can use resources like \"The Mediatrician's Guide\" to provide evidence-based advice for healthy digital engagement in children and address concerns about flat Earth beliefs among teenagers.", "citations": {"070da8dd-1499-4337-82d6-1a984c6dadd4_689668059": 1.0}}, {"text": "UNICEF recommends regulations to protect children from false information, and media literacy education is essential for youth.", "citations": {"7a10227e-4d21-4aa5-9188-8aaae5c21120_310740547": 1.0}}, {"text": "Exposure to hate speech and racism on social media harms youth, and social media-based racism and discrimination worsen mental health.", "citations": {"7a10227e-4d21-4aa5-9188-8aaae5c21120_310740547": 1.0}}, {"text": "Adolescent girls and minorities are disproportionately affected, and online harassment and cyberbullying are associated with depression.", "citations": {"7a10227e-4d21-4aa5-9188-8aaae5c21120_310740547": 1.0}}, {"text": "Social media companies must improve content moderation, and clinicians can help by reporting concerning content and promoting media literacy.", "citations": {"7a10227e-4d21-4aa5-9188-8aaae5c21120_310740547": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regular connection with children is vital for mental health, and open conversations about mental health reduce stigma.", "citations": {"ab671fff-5f9e-44c6-86de-ad25f586b608_10239409": 1.0}}, {"text": "Monitoring online activities is crucial for teenagers' well-being, and recognizing symptoms of mental health issues is essential.", "citations": {"ab671fff-5f9e-44c6-86de-ad25f586b608_10239409": 1.0}}, {"text": "Professional help is necessary for severe mental health concerns, and modeling positive mental health behavior helps children.", "citations": {"ab671fff-5f9e-44c6-86de-ad25f586b608_10239409": 1.0}}, {"text": "Close parent-child relationships act as a buffer in times of stress, and seeking help for own mental health issues is important.", "citations": {"ab671fff-5f9e-44c6-86de-ad25f586b608_10239409": 1.0}}, {"text": "Social media poses risks to young people's mental health, and nearly every teenager in America uses social media.", "citations": {"c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_619706829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Clinical depression in teens doubled between 2011 and 2021, and 25% of teenage girls had made a suicide plan in 2021.", "citations": {"c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_619706829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Social media use affects adolescents and causes anxiety, and adolescent girls are more at risk of social media impacts.", "citations": {"c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_619706829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Utah established a curfew for teens on social media apps, and lawmakers are pushing for restrictions on teens' social media use.", "citations": {"c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_619706829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the spread of misinformation, including flat Earth beliefs, is a significant concern for teenagers' mental health and well-being, and efforts should be made to promote critical thinking skills and media literacy, and to protect teenagers from the negative effects of misinformation.", "citations": {"613a83ef-3b15-4765-854b-5d60ed7cc56c_386227972": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"033e7078-07c7-4ddd-b9e5-a28f34f6a60b_219816380": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_669431569": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"ca40ec82-78d0-48df-a54a-d1734fe3a0b3_53647378": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"7614d155-5beb-49f4-b13a-4f2675a1d6c8_866557951": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"23318c83-eda0-48f0-a034-06b1ed01ea90_1005393558": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"234c0ac8-224a-4ae9-b9fc-df4652c033eb_450387180": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"3761fcd4-8573-4a21-aea5-1a28e1ba43c6_973881705": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"63f1436d-9b81-4d3a-a709-d113e61cd06c_494794498": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"7a5496ed-84de-4732-b7e8-140aa144dd55_614973336": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"97523098-62d0-4e63-b448-9caa86bcc1dd_60973377": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"a82fde8a-9e03-4821-93dd-3732d46d41c4_975752910": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"af07cd35-8c56-40f2-a245-85d82c52d4b9_576268285": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_95418142": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"f6eb21b5-aefb-47b5-a467-cf0ff072bc84_615722827": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"1794e4e9-24d7-4c79-be00-2fedf0c6b128_30859492": 1.0}}, {"text": ".", "citations": {"4a56