{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1023", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The global aerospace industry is shifting towards sustainability and efficiency, focusing on reducing carbon emissions.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The Asia-Pacific region is the largest market for single-aisle aircraft, while Europe is driving growth with demand for fuel-efficient options.", "citations": {"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global single-aisle aircraft market is expected to reach $222.20 billion by 2030, growing at a 12.5% CAGR.", "citations": {"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685": 1.0}}, {"text": "Airlines prioritize fuel-efficient aircraft.", "citations": {"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global fleet will reach 46,560 thousand aircraft and 3,230 thousand cargo ships by 2042.", "citations": {"5441001d-5c90-459e-ba13-63792d01320e_1052129711": 1.0}}, {"text": "From 2019-2042, passenger traffic is expected to grow at 3.6% and freight at 3.2%.", "citations": {"5441001d-5c90-459e-ba13-63792d01320e_1052129711": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing forecasts 44,000 aircraft by 2043, mostly single-aisle planes.", "citations": {"2ff4c61a-59c1-406b-a506-d4c10f66932f_241818403": 1.0}}, {"text": "Global demand for new aircraft is expected to reach 43,610 in 20 years, led by North America with 9,160 aircraft.", "citations": {"bf2732d0-bb7b-4e55-9d35-f1d548672746_296106203": 1.0}}, {"text": "Single-aisle aircraft will comprise 64% of the global passenger fleet, with over 32,500 new units demanded in the next 20 years.", "citations": {"bf2732d0-bb7b-4e55-9d35-f1d548672746_296106203": 1.0}}, {"text": "The world will need 19,000 new aircraft worth $3.2 trillion in the next decade, with the global fleet reaching over 49,000 by 2040.", "citations": {"bf2732d0-bb7b-4e55-9d35-f1d548672746_296106203": 1.0}}, {"text": "By 2040, China's and Asia Pacific's passenger shares are expected to grow to 20% and 21%, from 15% and 18%, respectively.", "citations": {"bf2732d0-bb7b-4e55-9d35-f1d548672746_296106203": 1.0}}, {"text": "New aircraft generations are 20% more fuel-efficient than their predecessors.", "citations": {"0ee40b49-f789-44f6-a404-d314b3000579_277383779": 1.0}}, {"text": "SAF is considered the most effective means to decarbonize aviation, with potential emissions reductions of 27% using 30% SAF.", "citations": {"0ee40b49-f789-44f6-a404-d314b3000579_277383779": 1.0}}, {"text": "Airbus aims for zero aviation emissions by 2050 through sustainable fuel and efficiency improvements.", "citations": {"513ef66e-085a-4865-9d81-62e5b51b62e4_491272360": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing is focusing on sustainable aviation fuels, with its CEO believing hydrogen aircraft won't be viable until 2050.", "citations": {"90ddd635-7761-48dd-91f8-e94698ecaa07_1018508608": 1.0}}, {"text": "Comac has 1000 firm orders for the C919 aircraft.", "citations": {"1c90c8ee-36a8-41ae-b16b-6740767f842a_25408251": 1.0}}, {"text": "Comac targets 150 annual C919 productions.", "citations": {"1c90c8ee-36a8-41ae-b16b-6740767f842a_25408251": 1.0}}, {"text": "Airbus has over \u20ac10 billion in net cash, while Boeing has $17 billion in negative net assets and $39 billion in debt.", "citations": {"89b86d44-c045-4a7e-bd6e-7655f3fc6466_642837187": 1.0}}, {"text": "Comac may break Airbus and Boeing's monopoly as it seeks certification for the C919.", "citations": {"c5d75a84-d3a1-42ee-8060-9f572c2be0e4_722279503": 1.0}}, {"text": "Airbus delivered 611 planes in 2021, surpassing Boeing's 302 deliveries.", "citations": {"cf432dbd-1483-46bb-bd1d-c9d0a26487d2_8871897": 1.0}}, {"text": "China is expected to need 8,560 new planes, including 6,470 narrowbodies, over the next 20 years.", "citations": {"c7b767c9-09fd-43c7-83f7-b07f61e38ae6_189472738": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing has $58 billion in debt and needs China deliveries to restart 737 production.", "citations": {"d69f7e62-1b2c-4bdb-9871-e932a2d87c1e_331030172": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing and Airbus are well-positioned to capitalize on future demand for new, fuel-efficient aircraft through investments in sustainable aviation fuel and electric propulsion.", "citations": {"a39da225-598b-4324-8178-2b00de26503e_453753553": 1.0}}, {"text": "Implementing sustainable aviation fuels and electric propulsion systems will significantly impact aircraft manufacturers and help reduce the aviation industry's greenhouse gas emissions.", "citations": {"ee2e17d1-b943-404d-b6f2-8d001455ed54_661739872": 1.0}}], "references": ["d69f7e62-1b2c-4bdb-9871-e932a2d87c1e_331030172", "ee2e17d1-b943-404d-b6f2-8d001455ed54_661739872", "c7b767c9-09fd-43c7-83f7-b07f61e38ae6_189472738", "89b86d44-c045-4a7e-bd6e-7655f3fc6466_642837187", "c5d75a84-d3a1-42ee-8060-9f572c2be0e4_722279503", "0ee40b49-f789-44f6-a404-d314b3000579_277383779", "5441001d-5c90-459e-ba13-63792d01320e_1052129711", "90ddd635-7761-48dd-91f8-e94698ecaa07_1018508608", "2ff4c61a-59c1-406b-a506-d4c10f66932f_241818403", "cf432dbd-1483-46bb-bd1d-c9d0a26487d2_8871897", "a39da225-598b-4324-8178-2b00de26503e_453753553", "bf2732d0-bb7b-4e55-9d35-f1d548672746_296106203", "1c90c8ee-36a8-41ae-b16b-6740767f842a_25408251", "513ef66e-085a-4865-9d81-62e5b51b62e4_491272360", "515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1024", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Boeing expects demand for 44,000 fuel-efficient aircraft by 2043, driven by replacement needs and growing travel demand.", "citations": {"2ff4c61a-59c1-406b-a506-d4c10f66932f_241818403": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Asia-Pacific region is the largest market for single-aisle aircraft, while Europe is the fastest-growing.", "citations": {"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global single-aisle aircraft market is expected to reach $222.20 billion by 2030, growing at a 12.5% CAGR.", "citations": {"515c5776-a50e-4782-835a-77bfb011b38e_922454685": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing forecasts 38,500 new aircraft in 20 years, with China, Europe, and North America needing 14.3, 7.8, and 7.3 thousand, respectively.", "citations": {"35bf81d9-8fb4-4f64-9478-54e28df42730_900060412": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Asia-Pacific region will drive aircraft demand, needing 17,620 new aircraft in 20 years, 70% of which will be single-aisle.", "citations": {"b7814f2f-30a3-475d-9024-479c2f67817b_166926857": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global aircraft fleet is expected to nearly double by 2043, with $2.9 trillion spent on 42,595 new planes by 2040.", "citations": {"5867527f-48e2-4543-921b-79edad641fbf_327309205": 1.0}}, {"text": "The demand for cargo planes is expected to increase 3.5% per year, with 3,500 freighter deliveries anticipated by 2042, growing the global fleet to 3,230 thousand.", "citations": {"65a6d821-4ded-4ba5-874a-2aa5ee48ba5e_72581204": 1.0}}, {"text": "From 2019-2042, average growth rates are expected to be 3.6% for passenger traffic and 3.2% for freight.", "citations": {"5441001d-5c90-459e-ba13-63792d01320e_1052129711": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aerospace industry aims for net-zero emissions by 2050.", "citations": {"0afd630d-2a2c-414c-b401-971dccb47c21_361076215": 1.0}}, {"text": "Etihad aims to halve its 2019 emissions by 2035, having already flown a flight with 72% reduced emissions.", "citations": {"0afd630d-2a2c-414c-b401-971dccb47c21_361076215": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global sustainable aviation fuel market is expected to reach USD 2987.5 million by 2027, growing at a CAGR of 72.4%.", "citations": {"15dbbde3-8146-4ee0-b763-10d0733a16bc_355311255": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aviation sector is adopting renewable jet fuels and hybrid-electric aircraft to reduce emissions.", "citations": {"15dbbde3-8146-4ee0-b763-10d0733a16bc_355311255": 1.0}}, {"text": "China and India are emerging air mobility markets, with local manufacturers competing with Boeing and Airbus.", "citations": {"0d10cb5d-1c05-44c8-aabb-51e7cd4294af_847617207": 1.0}}, {"text": "The C919 competes with Airbus and Boeing in emerging markets.", "citations": {"0d10cb5d-1c05-44c8-aabb-51e7cd4294af_847617207": 1.0}}, {"text": "Comac has received over 1,000 orders for the C919 and plans to produce 150 aircraft per year.", "citations": {"c78f9769-acc2-48e8-a416-1453063094a9_1007837346": 1.0}}, {"text": "China Eastern has ordered 100 C919 jets worth $9.9 billion from Comac.", "citations": {"c7b767c9-09fd-43c7-83f7-b07f61e38ae6_189472738": 1.0}}, {"text": "Comac relies heavily on Western suppliers, and C919 certifications are uncertain.", "citations": {"c78f9769-acc2-48e8-a416-1453063094a9_1007837346": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Department of Defense is investing in future warfare technology, including autonomous aircraft, with companies like ORB Aerospace.", "citations": {"083a8459-66b4-4246-ac7f-efecc1cbf190_514073649": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aerospace industry is expected to be impacted by emerging technologies like electric propulsion, led by companies such as magniX.", "citations": {"2bca460b-85a0-428b-8e5b-63bd1a70c671_11980799": 1.0}}, {"text": "magniX is pioneering electric aviation solutions with partners including AeroTEC and Air Tindi.", "citations": {"2bca460b-85a0-428b-8e5b-63bd1a70c671_11980799": 1.0}}, {"text": "Integrating sustainable fuels and electric propulsion into aircraft requires significant technical modifications.", "citations": {"185aa265-fafc-4dc5-8410-3dfd9cf914fe_444262621": 1.0}}, {"text": "Liebherr-Aerospace is developing systems for zero-emission aircraft, including a hydrogen test bench in Toulouse.", "citations": {"185aa265-fafc-4dc5-8410-3dfd9cf914fe_444262621": 1.0}}, {"text": "Air New Zealand aims to fly a zero-emissions plane by 2026, partnering with four aircraft makers to develop electric, hydrogen, and hybrid aircraft.", "citations": {"1b49dc6b-f9bc-426c-a5fd-9a670ba1fc1d_795970172": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aviation industry's decarbonization efforts are hindered by a scarce supply of sustainable aviation fuel (SAF).", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "The SAF market faces competition with renewable diesel for resources.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "SAFs could make up 7.5 percent of jet fuel demand by 2030, with airlines setting adoption targets for that year.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "National governments are setting policies to support domestic SAF adoption, driving market growth.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "SAF production raises concerns about biodiversity and climate implications.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "The SAF market lacks technological diversification, a major barrier to widespread adoption.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "Current technology limitations make airline decarbonization plans unrealistic without significant research investment.", "citations": {"125fe24b-4acd-4f62-9416-5908a641d534_214878589": 1.0}}, {"text": "The public supports future flight technologies, but has concerns about safety, cybersecurity, and privacy.", "citations": {"12d9d4c8-91d8-4490-a011-119a8e01ecfc_968649365": 1.0}}, {"text": "Governance and regulation are needed to constrain these technologies due to accessibility and affordability concerns.", "citations": {"12d9d4c8-91d8-4490-a011-119a8e01ecfc_968649365": 1.0}}, {"text": "Environmental concerns, such as wildlife and air pollution, need to be addressed.", "citations": {"12d9d4c8-91d8-4490-a011-119a8e01ecfc_968649365": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aviation industry aims to reach net zero carbon emissions by 2050, with a target to halve emissions by the same year.", "citations": {"353c1940-9198-4ada-af6c-f86d5632b8b0_707549829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Aircraft manufacturers and fuel producers are developing more efficient technologies and sustainable aviation fuels.", "citations": {"353c1940-9198-4ada-af6c-f86d5632b8b0_707549829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Governments are supporting the industry's emission reduction efforts through initiatives like the International Air Transport Carbon Offset plan.", "citations": {"353c1940-9198-4ada-af6c-f86d5632b8b0_707549829": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU requires 2% of aviation fuel to be environmentally friendly by 2025, increasing to 70% by 2050.", "citations": {"4935bc39-e6ed-4768-bba2-f2789433cf19_414528207": 1.0}}, {"text": "Green fuel production is currently 2-4 times more expensive than traditional fuel.", "citations": {"4935bc39-e6ed-4768-bba2-f2789433cf19_414528207": 1.0}}, {"text": "China aims for new energy aircraft to be mainstream by 2035, with milestones set for 2025.", "citations": {"24b5190a-056e-412e-8f76-cf3223f6d336_725979455": 1.0}}, {"text": "Electric and hydrogen energy aircraft are expected to enter commercial applications by 2025.", "citations": {"24b5190a-056e-412e-8f76-cf3223f6d336_725979455": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aerospace industry is growing rapidly with the adoption of additive manufacturing.", "citations": {"8f06c7be-b7ba-44fe-99b0-b7f1cd50aca7_246353187": 1.0}}, {"text": "Qualification hurdles hinder the adoption of additive manufacturing in aerospace.", "citations": {"8f06c7be-b7ba-44fe-99b0-b7f1cd50aca7_246353187": 1.0}}, {"text": "The aviation industry faces significant challenges in achieving net zero emissions by 2050, with 76% of respondents citing sustainability as a factor changing their work.", "citations": {"94e91a67-fc8b-4442-968e-05b655a5f411_737539653": 1.0}}, {"text": "30% of respondents see sustainability as the industry's biggest challenge.", "citations": {"94e91a67-fc8b-4442-968e-05b655a5f411_737539653": 1.0}}, {"text": "88% of companies are adopting sustainability strategies, with 46% expecting the industry to reach net zero emissions by 2050.", "citations": {"94e91a67-fc8b-4442-968e-05b655a5f411_737539653": 1.0}}, {"text": "Government support is key to accelerating aviation sustainability, with sustainable jet fuel a top priority.", "citations": {"94e91a67-fc8b-4442-968e-05b655a5f411_737539653": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing and Airbus are facing supply chain problems disrupting jetliner production.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_818444990": 1.0}}, {"text": "The 737 jet's production may be delayed by one to two months.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_818444990": 1.0}}, {"text": "New jet designs are unlikely to be introduced before the mid-2030s due to slow development of emerging technology.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_818444990": 1.0}}, {"text": "Industry stakeholders advise companies to develop sustainable platforms now to prepare for the future.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_818444990": 1.0}}, {"text": "Electric planes could reduce operating costs by 80 percent, with the airline industry making up 2.1 percent of human-induced carbon dioxide emissions.", "citations": {"ab2cc3e9-01c4-4096-8d87-226fa4f2b437_1027095428": 1.0}}, {"text": "Aviation aims for net-zero emissions by 2050, but electric planes face battery and certification challenges.", "citations": {"ab2cc3e9-01c4-4096-8d87-226fa4f2b437_1027095428": 1.0}}, {"text": "Boeing predicts smaller electric planes by the 2030s, and Uber's flying taxi service possibly by 2023.", "citations": {"ab2cc3e9-01c4-4096-8d87-226fa4f2b437_1027095428": 1.0}}, {"text": "Airbus has partnered with Neste, the world's largest sustainable aviation fuel producer, to increase SAF availability.", "citations": {"ee2e17d1-b943-404d-b6f2-8d001455ed54_661739872": 1.0}}, {"text": "Current aircraft are certified for 50 percent SAF, with Airbus targeting 100 percent by decade's end.", "citations": {"ee2e17d1-b943-404d-b6f2-8d001455ed54_661739872": 1.0}}, {"text": "Doroni Aerospace will unveil a revolutionary eVTOL on March 1st to transform urban air mobility.", "citations": {"07e3001d-02e9-4fd6-93c5-297d45a1360e_135019147": 1.0}}, {"text": "Doron Merdinger's 2016 company aims to democratize flight while prioritizing safety and sustainability.", "citations": {"07e3001d-02e9-4fd6-93c5-297d45a1360e_135019147": 1.0}}, {"text": "Japan has invested $33 billion in hydrogen-fueled aviation, aiming to launch hydrogen-fueled aircraft by 2035.", "citations": {"08d63595-1789-413d-9e6d-b22cf4bbc7ff_667954234": 1.0}}, {"text": "India's first fifth-generation fighter jet, the AMCA, is under development, with a prototype expected three years after project approval.", "citations": {"1287df68-6b5a-4953-a796-97dc10adbe92_670551898": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Indian Air Force plans to buy at least 120 AMCA fighters by 2035, with the first flight expected in 2026-27.", "citations": {"1287df68-6b5a-4953-a796-97dc10adbe92_670551898": 1.0}}, {"text": "New energy aircraft are expected to become mainstream by 2035, with domestic and electric models entering use by 2025.", "citations": {"24b5190a-056e-412e-8f76-cf3223f6d336_725979455": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rolls Royce has completed tests on a hydrogen-powered engine, which could reduce carbon emissions and is seen as the future of short-haul aviation by easyJet's CEO.", "citations": {"311b0bd6-313b-4534-8c8e-5cad39892ab0_927106034": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Airlander 10 is expected to start hybrid-electric operation in 2026 and all-electric in 2030.", "citations": {"3e13f82a-3311-41a4-90ee-843be2bee6dc_859341427": 1.0}}, {"text": "NASA has partnered with Pratt & Whitney to develop low-emission aviation engine technology, aiming to reduce fuel consumption and emissions by 2050.", "citations": {"6931d0ef-3408-4b28-9adc-e0c28f5e89b9_585110424": 1.0}}, {"text": "NASA and Boeing are partnering to create a fuel-efficient aircraft aiming to reduce emissions by 30%, with a first test flight expected in 2028.", "citations": {"a7b3981c-68e9-4d1d-9996-256dff4462eb_936719364": 1.0}}, {"text": "The NGAD is expected to replace the F-22 Raptor, with a contract award in 2024 and production by decade's end, using open-architecture standards.", "citations": {"a7b50f51-50af-4d3b-a12e-d1472ab4a94e_138611627": 1.0}}, {"text": "NASA's X-66A test flight is set for 2028, targeting 30% reduced emissions and 50% of the commercial market by 2035.", "citations": {"b639435f-99b7-479c-9884-7466d11352ba_166330628": 1.0}}, {"text": "Aircraft development is expected to focus on high energy and intelligence, incorporating technologies like metamaterials and adaptive engines.", "citations": {"f3b24342-5671-4d85-a812-56608e542295_86608218": 1.0}}, {"text": "China's general aviation equipment supply capacity is expected to improve significantly by 2027 and a new industry model by 2030.", "citations": {"fa56b545-7fd4-4147-9905-8c732476766f_911150548": 1.0}}, {"text": "Electrification is expected to be the main direction of industrial technological innovation, promoting airworthiness and intelligent air travel by 2030.", "citations": {"fa56b545-7fd4-4147-9905-8c732476766f_911150548": 1.0}}], "references": ["b7814f2f-30a3-475d-9024-479c2f67817b_166926857", "35bf81d9-8fb4-4f64-9478-54e28df42730_900060412", "083a8459-66b4-4246-ac7f-efecc1cbf190_514073649", "c78f9769-acc2-48e8-a416-1453063094a9_1007837346", "2ff4c61a-59c1-406b-a506-d4c10f