{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1025", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Women are increasingly becoming crane operators, challenging a historically male-dominated industry.", "citations": {"14d2b2e8-59cd-4d3e-ab35-cf57fee10e78_86706736": 1.0}}, {"text": "Elena Badaeva, a female crane operator with over 30 years of experience, is an example of a woman succeeding in this field, operating at 40 meters to construct houses in several cities.", "citations": {"14d2b2e8-59cd-4d3e-ab35-cf57fee10e78_86706736": 1.0}}, {"text": "Women in construction bring diverse knowledge and experiences, but recruiting them requires girls to take math and science courses.", "citations": {"c6691d00-dfb0-4b34-8d9d-a1453a0429a1_717856038": 1.0}}, {"text": "Role models and companies like Suffolk encourage girls to join the field through diversity programs.", "citations": {"c6691d00-dfb0-4b34-8d9d-a1453a0429a1_717856038": 1.0}}, {"text": "Labor shortages are leading companies to hire qualified women, who can be valuable in construction due to their attention to detail.", "citations": {"c6691d00-dfb0-4b34-8d9d-a1453a0429a1_717856038": 1.0}}, {"text": "Female crane operators are achieving success and contributing to greater gender equality and diversity in the industry.", "citations": {"3a8cbfea-9ef3-4a87-b89f-73c826c436b8_140000997": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tata Steel is promoting diversity by hiring women as operators and providing them with training.", "citations": {"c0c71277-9cd7-4a17-a7c0-7bea6832abbc_141479220": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Ministry of Labor now allows women to work as crane drivers, among other previously prohibited professions.", "citations": {"7eb81049-0a87-41be-95e3-2dfd47b4aeca_72244829": 1.0}}, {"text": "Women in construction face greater risks and lower average salaries than men, highlighting the need for greater support and protection.", "citations": {"5d510a0c-546d-4abc-b754-de4153cf36ae_716225683": 1.0}}, {"text": "Targeted programs can increase women's participation in construction, with some companies promoting diversity and inclusion.", "citations": {"0b355931-0713-4d9e-9d44-8fb722aa6392_153470386": 1.0}}, {"text": "Leighton promotes diversity and inclusion through policies like paid parental leave, flexible work, and female career development training.", "citations": {"59a811e7-464f-49b1-91a4-205335ed2127_1064480777": 1.0}}, {"text": "Achieving gender parity in the construction industry could generate $20bn-$40bn GDP for countries like New Zealand.", "citations": {"0b355931-0713-4d9e-9d44-8fb722aa6392_153470386": 1.0}}, {"text": "In the US, women hold 13% of construction payroll jobs, a percentage that has remained stagnant since the 1990s.", "citations": {"e54d5d6e-0c6a-47f4-9834-81419f13a22e_14234603": 1.0}}, {"text": "Initiatives like on-the-job training and apprenticeships can help recruit and retain women in construction.", "citations": {"e54d5d6e-0c6a-47f4-9834-81419f13a22e_14234603": 1.0}}, {"text": "Barratt Developments and other companies are creating a family-friendly culture and opportunities for women in construction.", "citations": {"f73c1329-0b74-4166-9635-b300ed83ff84_963588351": 1.0}}, {"text": "The construction industry is seeing positive trends towards greater gender equality, with women taking on non-traditional roles.", "citations": {"18936b99-e516-4cca-b846-d29e85b6c832_522368479": 1.0}}, {"text": "The maritime sector has increased women's inclusion by establishing gender-neutral frameworks.", "citations": {"02734096-17ba-4798-88b0-4e734752dc20_582620589": 1.0}}, {"text": "The International Maritime Organisation (IMO) launched its Gender Diversity Programme in 1988 to promote gender equality in the maritime sector.", "citations": {"02734096-17ba-4798-88b0-4e734752dc20_582620589": 1.0}}, {"text": "Women face challenges in maritime leadership, but their empowerment is a growing trend.", "citations": {"16360a9e-3863-4b7d-9bad-f42c562e4fb5_1047218848": 1.0}}, {"t