{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1031", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Africa received $83 billion in foreign direct investment in 2021, mostly from Europeans.", "citations": {"da89937a-32d7-40db-beb3-46050cdb3c6d_927341125": 1.0}}, {"text": "The UK and France invested $65 billion and $60 billion, respectively, in Africa.", "citations": {"da89937a-32d7-40db-beb3-46050cdb3c6d_927341125": 1.0}}, {"text": "North Africa's foreign direct investment fell 5% to $9.3 billion in 2021.", "citations": {"da89937a-32d7-40db-beb3-46050cdb3c6d_927341125": 1.0}}, {"text": "Egypt's foreign direct investment decreased by 5.35% in 2020, but still attracted $8.14 billion in 2018.", "citations": {"019009cf-b145-4bf1-a6f0-f75d261445c2_241982001": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country is expected to receive $16.5 billion in foreign direct investment in 2024-2025 from various sectors.", "citations": {"77626304-23cc-441b-b824-e3da7700ee4a_182209447": 1.0}}, {"text": "The construction sector had the largest share of capital value in Egypt in 2021/2022, with 31.2 thousand companies established.", "citations": {"bbdc486e-23aa-4e36-a5b3-a2963ab02c1c_57222322": 1.0}}, {"text": "Renewable energy projects reached 71 in 2021, worth $39 billion.", "citations": {"da89937a-32d7-40db-beb3-46050cdb3c6d_927341125": 1.0}}, {"text": "The African Investment Forum coordinated $32.8 billion in investments, including a $15.6 billion deal for the Lagos-Abidjan highway.", "citations": {"5bfeb426-e80d-45e0-9fc1-d9c7182c9abb_187276660": 1.0}}, {"text": "The UK's BII plans to invest $60 billion in Africa over five years in renewable power and digital infrastructure.", "citations": {"e3d3bec1-19f0-4d60-a67f-c8cb4d639ade_764369635": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mozambique's foreign direct investment rose 68% to $5.102 billion in 2021, surpassing Nigeria's $4.844 billion, which increased 103%.", "citations": {"a5d99f5d-5340-4171-8450-24720fdfb69e_898064754": 1.0}}, {"text": "Major foreign companies like Eni, Apache, and BP have invested $12.6 billion in Egypt's oil and gas sector.", "citations": {"144428a7-e284-44de-9df0-7d707b3a138d_463674264": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US plans to invest $33 billion in Africa, with Marriott and General Electric contributing $14 billion.", "citations": {"84ceb796-4153-4342-8ec2-f1ccf962ca23_314148496": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU plans to invest $150 billion in Africa's infrastructure through the Global Gateway initiative.", "citations": {"940b83f7-af87-4242-9615-8597f9087952_786010691": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google has invested $1 billion in Africa's digital transformation.", "citations": {"100ec187-499c-4e90-9c2e-c8bcbc89b665_79045555": 1.0}}, {"text": "The AfCFTA agreement aims to create a single continental market by eliminating tariffs and trade constraints.", "citations": {"0145b903-72e4-412b-a3e1-c9f74ac51fbf_307445772": 1.0}}, {"text": "The African Continental Free Trade Agreement has 54 member states and came into effect in 2018.", "citations": {"0145b903-72e4-412b-a3e1-c9f74ac51fbf_307445772": 1.0}}, {"text": "The IFC aims to mobilize $10 billion in private investment into Africa annually by 2030.", "citations": {"bb0d49c4-4a1b-43ea-9ae0-cf04b288f503_375741834": 1.0}}, {"text": "The African Finance Corporation has invested over $10 billion in 37 African countries.", "citations": {"ce022d69-a4e7-4f36-b9f2-22ecf4236dac_377947921": 1.0}}, {"text": "Africa needs $3 trillion by 2030 to address climate change, having already suffered $70 billion in drought-related losses.", "citations": {"fc07e9ea-49bf-4ca1-bf7a-067037d6236d_195767128": 1.0}}, {"text": "The AfCFTA aims to create a single market of 1.3 billion people with $3.4 trillion GDP.", "citations": {"a948934f-cc3e-4b6b-ba17-7748e34ef2c6_397268782": 1.0}}, {"text": "De-risking and local currency financing are crucial to attract private investment in African infrastructure.", "citations": {"b0993337-fb9a-43cb-a8fe-1ded47b0a813_1009547743": 1.0}}], "references": 