{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1077", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Argentina's President Javier Milei has introduced economic reforms to overhaul the economy and reduce debt.", "citations": {"52c92711-e0f3-4cd0-ba75-2ec03fb794c4_67143469": 1.0}}, {"text": "His economic plan aims to cut spending, reduce inflation, and privatize state companies to achieve a zero-deficit target this year.", "citations": {"52c92711-e0f3-4cd0-ba75-2ec03fb794c4_67143469": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei has proposed dollarizing Argentina's economy to combat inflation.", "citations": {"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091": 1.0}}, {"text": "The plan has been met with opposition due to concerns it could compromise the country's monetary policy and leave it vulnerable to external shocks.", "citations": {"4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei remains committed to his economic reform plan, which includes deregulation, free-market reforms, and granting the president special powers.", "citations": {"2b0ec783-b30c-4f0b-bf5a-5aaa821391eb_219792461": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has deregulated the economy and proposed privatizing state-run enterprises to boost investment and business incentives.", "citations": {"2a1072be-ae9d-4584-a0eb-b9f28d881bf3_245687516": 1.0}}, {"text": "The economic reform plan includes abolishing ministries and reducing government employees to improve efficiency.", "citations": {"08d63595-1789-413d-9e6d-b22cf4bbc7ff_539685673": 1.0}}, {"text": "The reduction of government employees is expected to save the budget, but may impact healthcare and education services.", "citations": {"9b0d7d5a-bb2b-4fe8-8be8-2ca44eaabab5_308219554": 1.0}}, {"text": "A decree to repeal over 300 laws and a 664-article omnibus bill have been sent to Congress.", "citations": {"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986": 1.0}}, {"text": "The bill proposes environmental law reforms and grants the executive over 1,000 powers until 2025.", "citations": {"de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government awaits a presidential decree to liberalize the economy by amending or repealing over 300 restrictions.", "citations": {"e1559805-84f4-461f-a43f-9f4f3ac92c08_821341269": 1.0}}, {"text": "The decree will modernize labor law and remove restrictions in sectors like tourism and trade to facilitate job creation.", "citations": {"e1559805-84f4-461f-a43f-9f4f3ac92c08_821341269": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government's economic reforms face opposition from regional governors and protesters.", "citations": {"2b0ec783-b30c-4f0b-bf5a-5aaa821391eb_219792461": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government faces challenges meeting its zero-deficit pledge amidst 200%-plus inflation and capital controls.", "citations": {"52c92711-e0f3-4cd0-ba75-2ec03fb794c4_67143469": 1.0}}, {"text": "Argentina's economy faces stagflation, with the IMF predicting a 2.8% contraction in 2024.", "citations": {"94495d54-f24e-4971-a019-9bc95db48869_200169402": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Senate has approved President Javier Milei's overhaul and tax bills, granting him broad powers in several areas.", "citations": {"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677": 1.0}}, {"text": "The reforms have been criticized for their potential impact on vulnerable populations, with Argentina's 40 percent poverty rate and 160 percent inflation making safeguards essential.", "citations": {"453bb4aa-916e-409e-95e9-03e4379d9f33_136307475": 1.0}}, {"text": "Labor unions have promised a nationwide strike, while opposition deputy Hugo Yasky has criticized Milei's austerity reforms.", "citations": {"474c6eec-ebe5-4196-bca0-46e92bb6f014_959262116": 1.0}}, {"text": "The success of the reforms will depend on effective implementation and the response of the opposition and other stakeholders.", "citations": {"2b0ec783-b30c-4f0b-bf5a-5aaa821391eb_219792461": 1.0}}, {"text": "The international community will closely watch Argentina's economic reforms, which will significantly impact its economic future.", "citations": {"9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677": 1.0}}], "references": ["4b67c948-7841-4206-b5b8-acbb37d68ba2_104775091", "453bb4aa-916e-409e-95e9-03e4379d9f33_136307475", "2a1072be-ae9d-4584-a0eb-b9f28d881bf3_245687516", "e1559805-84f4-461f-a43f-9f4f3ac92c08_821341269", "9b0d7d5a-bb2b-4fe8-8be8-2ca44eaabab5_308219554", "08d63595-1789-413d-9e6d-b22cf4bbc7ff_539685673", "94495d54-f24e-4971-a019-9bc95db48869_200169402", "de62bbf7-5a19-4522-a025-9cc9f72e3f03_277776986", "474c6eec-ebe5-4196-bca0-46e92bb6f014_959262116", "9fc4b03d-d2ab-4085-b5cd-35010d1019fd_29738677", "52c92711-e0f3-4cd0-ba75-2ec03fb794c4_67143469", "2b0ec783-b30c-4f0b-bf5a-5aaa821391eb_219792461"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1078", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Argentina's new president, Javier Milei, has introduced economic reforms to tackle high inflation and poverty.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "His policies, including slashing state spending and privatizing state-owned entities, have sparked controversy and protests.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Milei's plan includes replacing the peso with the US dollar to curb hyperinflation and stabilize the economy.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Argentina's plan to replace pesos with US dollars lacks funds and requires congressional approval and a constitutional change.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Dollarization may take up to two years to implement and could increase Argentina's inflation rate.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Milei's government has introduced a decree deregulating the economy, repealing over 350 regulations, and allowing privatization of 40 public companies, sparking widespread protests.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The government's economic reforms have been praised for liberalizing the economy, but criticized for threatening social welfare and workers' rights.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The success of Milei's economic reforms will depend on effective implementation, opposition response, and their economic and social impact.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The government's privatization plans and subsidy cuts may significantly impact healthcare, education, energy, low-income households, and the overall economy.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Reducing subsidies and privatizing state-owned companies may increase prices, exacerbate poverty, and lead to job losses and declining public services.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The government's economic reforms also aim to promote growth, reduce poverty, and increase investment.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The economic reforms will require careful planning to ensure equitable benefits and