{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1079", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Dr. Jane Goodall's work promotes conservation and sustainability education, notably through her Roots and Shoots program, which empowers young people in 68 countries.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program promotes holistic helping of the environment, people, and animals to inspire hope and positive change.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "Jane Goodall believes individual actions and climate innovation can change the world.", "citations": {"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Roots and Shoots program teaches students about environmental issues and promotes holistic thinking to help the environment, people, and animals.", "citations": {"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871": 1.0}}, {"text": "Incorporating Roots and Shoots into a high school curriculum helps students understand environmental issues and make a positive impact.", "citations": {"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program offers hands-on activities like planting trees and exploring nature to enhance learning.", "citations": {"f2e4d3cb-381d-4587-be7b-ba0f26ac4b62_338441478": 1.0}}, {"text": "Jane Goodall's work and Roots and Shoots can significantly promote environmental awareness and community involvement in high school students.", "citations": {"f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Jane Goodall Institute's Conservation Asia project promotes conservation in Taiwan, Malaysia, and India from 2021 to 2025.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_55984504": 1.0}}, {"text": "The project includes establishing the Jane Goodall Sustainability Academy in Taiwan to promote conservation education.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_55984504": 1.0}}, {"text": "Conservation and sustainability education programs in high schools promote environmental awareness, responsibility, and career options.", "citations": {"05485d42-eb1c-440d-89fc-fefbe908b608_246438164": 1.0, "2f568ade-a549-46d0-847d-7055e1d87e0a_523850318": 0.5, "3f326164-a488-4023-afa8-3b3462be323a_825107167": 0.25, "4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_55984504": 0.125, "56fe4897-3d56-4641-a193-1094f87803c4_337324640": 0.0625, "5858b154-e095-483e-9dc9-d978d11190c9_414227532": 0.03125, "8cb22014-9312-4e6a-97b2-acd26caeba44_174748362": 0.015625}}, {"text": "Jane Goodall's Roots and Shoots program inspires youth to care for the environment in 68 countries through youth-led conservation projects.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program promotes holistic helping and empowers young people to make an impact on the environment, people, and animals.", "citations": {"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Jane Goodall Institute promotes conservation education, including Asia's first conservation-focused primary school in Taiwan, and supports efforts in Malaysia and India.", "citations": {"4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_55984504": 1.0}}, {"text": "Roots and Shoots teaches young people to work together for community-led conservation and positive change.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program aims to inspire young people to take environmental action, with Jane Goodall hoping to have Roots and Shoots in every school globally.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}], "references": ["4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183", "f2e4d3cb-381d-4587-be7b-ba0f26ac4b62_338441478", "05485d42-eb1c-440d-89fc-fefbe908b608_246438164", "4c0ee3ad-3947-4c32-9bdc-e1ea45fa3dd9_55984504", "95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871", "5858b154-e095-483e-9dc9-d978d11190c9_414227532", "2f568ade-a549-46d0-847d-7055e1d87e0a_523850318", "56fe4897-3d56-4641-a193-1094f87803c4_337324640", "8cb22014-9312-4e6a-97b2-acd26caeba44_174748362", "f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399", "3f326164-a488-4023-afa8-3b3462be323a_825107167"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1080", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Jane Goodall's current conservation efforts are focused on creating locally managed forests and community-centred conservation projects through the Jane Goodall Institute.", "citations": {"033e7078-07c7-4ddd-b9e5-a28f34f6a60b_1025705740": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Jane Goodall Institute is involved in various projects, including the TACARE project, which encourages woodlot planting and facilitates village land-use plans with USAID funding.", "citations": {"033e7078-07c7-4ddd-b9e5-a28f34f6a60b_1025705740": 1.0}}, {"text": "Dr. Jane Goodall has warned of a bleak future without action and has attended the COP15 global biodiversity summit to raise awareness about the issue.", "citations": {"1fa58c5e-416a-418f-8de6-22f4a81873e8_687307734": 1.0}}, {"text": "She has also campaigned to ban trophy hunting and has emphasized the importance of healthy ecosystems for human well-being.", "citations": {"1fa58c5e-416a-418f-8de6-22f4a81873e8_687307734": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Roots & Shoots program, founded by Dr. Jane Goodall, has over 8,000 sub-groups in 140 countries and promotes global environmental peace.", "citations": {"47120e3f-95ae-4a83-9c70-69d4b9024a90_952519686": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program inspires young people to care for the environment and is active in 68 countries worldwide, helping animals, people, and the environment.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "Roots & Shoots encourages young people to take action for conservation and aims to stop species extinction through collective action.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program empowers children to choose conservation projects and fosters community-led conservation and research.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "Dr. Jane Goodall hopes to expand Roots & Shoots to every school, and the program is part of the Jane Goodall Institute.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Roots & Shoots program operates in 68 countries to help animals, people, and the environment, empowering children to take action on conservation issues.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program focuses on endangered species and environmental conservation, with Jane Goodall hoping it inspires young people to make a difference.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "Roots & Shoots encourages collective action to address conservation issues, aiming to give people hope and inspire positive change.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program helps animals on the brink of extinction, such as the black robin, and human intervention can reverse the course of species extinction, as seen in success stories.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "Collective action can make a difference in conservation efforts, as demonstrated by the Roots & Shoots program.", "citations": {"4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program is active in 70 countries, empowering young people to create change and addressing major concerns such as climate change and loss of biodiversity.", "citations": {"95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Roots & Shoots program, founded by Jane Goodall, aims to empower young people to make a positive change in their communities and has been adapted for use in various settings, including high schools.", "citations": {"f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399": 1.0}}, {"text": "The program operates in over 60 countries and educates young people on environmental issues, making it a relevant and effective tool for high school students.", "citations": {"f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399": 1.0}}, {"text": "High school students can participate in conservation-focused lesson plans and activities, such as planting trees and shrubs along streambanks, which helps to protect soil from erosion and provide shade.", "citations": {"2f26054e-8106-4596-95db-105ebbf9b9e7_635550532": 1.0}}, {"text": "Students can also lead conservation projects and community outreach, such as building nesting boxes and water filtration, in partnership with organizations like Ducks Unlimited.", "citations": {"2f568ade-a549-46d0-847d-7055e1d87e0a_523850318": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Envirothon competition is another example of a conservation-focused activity for high school students, where they participate in hands-on activities like measuring trees and identifying birds.", "citations": {"4dbb144c-becd-4c99-a386-f6a9091eb946_204533047": 1.0}}, {"text": "Creating a butterfly garden for monarch habitat restoration is also a successful conservation-focused lesson plan, where students can learn about ecosystems and habitat destruction.", "citations": {"524202a2-9895-4a11-af64-96db15bee7ed_299247708": 1.0}}, {"text": "A bioblitz of an outdoor classroom area is another example of a conservation-focused activity, where students can restore the area by controlling invasive species and planting native plants.", "citations": {"75d22252-850a-4493-b9de-500653243cdd_474458198": 1.0}}, {"text": "High school students can also participate in community projects, such as creating dog beds from tires for animal shelters, which promotes environmental sustainability and community service.", "citations": {"78791118-f9c5-4ecd-b7a2-e57dcecfb197_965235224": 1.0}}, {"text": "The MiniCop event is an example of a conservation-focused activity, where students participate in litter picking, craft bird nesting boxes, and learn about tree identification and forest fire risks.", "citations": {"84ceb796-4153-4342-8ec2-f1ccf962ca23_586493794": 1.0}}, {"text": "Learning about invasive species, such as Japanese barberry, and participating in removal efforts is another example of a conservation-focused lesson plan.", "citations": {"8fb011ba-fad8-4061-9d78-5faa6c2bc8f4_718318156": 1.0}}, {"text": "Students can also participate in conservation carnivals, where they can design interactive game booths and learn about recycling and waste reduction.", "citations": {"ae11a0a0-0005-4f02-9a57-94eb92160789_95364913": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Marine Ecology Classroom provides hands-on learning for high school students, where they can learn about coral breeding and conservation, and monitor water level and temperature through mobile apps.", "citations": {"bd2b85ac-2a96-4889-904c-c127016f4056_109843297": 1.0}}, {"text": "The bear conservation unit in the curriculum of Kodiak High School is another example of a conservation-focused lesson plan, where students can learn about bear physiology and ecology, and practice bear encounters with simulations and costumes.", "citations": {"e6c1a6fa-7432-4fd3-ae9c-68a46ba517b9_918643323": 1.0}}], "references": ["e6c1a6fa-7432-4fd3-ae9c-68a46ba517b9_918643323", "2f26054e-8106-4596-95db-105ebbf9b9e7_635550532", "47120e3f-95ae-4a83-9c70-69d4b9024a90_952519686", "1fa58c5e-416a-418f-8de6-22f4a81873e8_687307734", "8fb011ba-fad8-4061-9d78-5faa6c2bc8f4_718318156", "ae11a0a0-0005-4f02-9a57-94eb92160789_95364913", "f684acbb-658a-47ca-aaad-05e0fb187180_520597399", "75d22252-850a-4493-b9de-500653243cdd_474458198", "524202a2-9895-4a11-af64-96db15bee7ed_299247708", "95f67cee-331c-42fd-9d52-cb7bad432c19_898632871", "2f568ade-a549-46d0-847d-7055e1d87e0a_523850318", "84ceb796-4153-4342-8ec2-f1ccf962ca23_586493794", "bd2b85ac-2a96-4889-904c-c127016f4056_109843297", "4ba15d10-6c38-48a0-8bc6-a4acdc286647_602215183", "78791118-f9c5-4ecd-b7a2-e57dcecfb197_965235224", "4dbb144c-becd-4c99-a386-f6a9091eb946_204533047", "033e7078-07c7-4ddd-b9e5-a28f34f6a60b_1025705740"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1081", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "China has achieved quantum computing superiority in superconducting and photonic systems, developing prototypes like \"Zuchongzhi II\" and \"Jiuchang II\".", "citations": {"063e477f-f6cb-4caf-92f0-2e8f0ac78ac1_133550004": 1.0}}, {"text": "China leads in quantum computing, with its Zuchongzhi No. 2 being 10 million times faster than the fastest supercomputer.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0}}, {"text": "China invested $15.3 billion in quantum technologies, with $2.35 billion in startup funding and 1,600 patents issued in 2022.", "citations": {"9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656": 1.0}}, {"text": "The University of Chicago and Tokyo are partnering on a quantum supercomputer aiming for 100,000 qubits, surpassing the current industry standard of around 430 qubits.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM has a 433-qubit machine, and a University of Chicago and Tokyo partnership is expected to yield breakthroughs in 2-3 years.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM leads in quantum systems, delivering a 1,000-qubit chip in 2023, while Intel applies transistor-based design, and IonQ is developing trapped ion quantum systems with 74 US patents.", "citations": {"6e8266d8-b5ac-4c3a-a99c-09a11714a059_58364063": 1.0}}, {"text": "Canada leads in quantum computing, investing $40 million in Xanadu Quantum Technologies to develop a photonic-based fault-tolerant quantum computer and over $1 billion in quantum research.", "citations": {"9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97dc-b43dfad3d708_10087775": 1.0}}, {"text": "IQM Quantum Computers is supplying quantum processing units for Spain's first quantum computer, led by Qilimanjaro Quantum Tech.", "citations": {"e31393d9-7567-4f4e-ba7b-0a8fe577432b_406052063": 1.0}}, {"text": "Germany's Quantum Valley Lower Saxony project, funded with \u20ac2 billion, aims to build a quantum computer by 2025, attracting 400 researchers.", "citations": {"e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US and China are investing $170 billion and at least $150 billion, respectively, in emerging technologies like AI and quantum computing.", "citations": {"e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has approved a \u20b96,003 crore National Quantum Mission to develop intermediate-scale quantum computers.", "citations": {"fe23f7b6-56e1-4326-be6d-fe65b3ed0b89_513447477": 1.0}}, {"text": "The UAE is investing in quantum computing, a market expected to reach $1 trillion by 2035, and the global quantum computing market is expected to reach $1.77 billion by 2026. [10].", "citations": {"5aa85504-fa86-4fc3-9eb3-db0ec081b8b2_180162801": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google, IBM, and Honeywell are investing heavily in research and development, including IBM's focus on quantum chip miniaturization and accuracy, and IBM plans to launch a 4,000-plus qubit machine by 2025. [5].", "citations": {"1c816133-af53-461a-b028-33ce9d1a9723_169809": 1.0}}, {"text": "The market is expected to grow at a 36.89% CAGR from 2022 to 2032, led by North America, particularly the US.", "citations": {"9d67d90b-c58f-4444-aaaa-88164c533333_281634985": 1.0}}], "references": ["4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054", "063e477f-f6cb-4caf-92f0-2e8f0ac78ac1_133550004", "9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656", "e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158", "e31393d9-7567-4f4e-ba7b-0a8fe577432b_406052063", "5aa85504-fa86-4fc3-9eb3-db0ec081b8b2_180162801", "6e8266d8-b5ac-4c3a-a99c-09a11714a059_58364063", "1c816133-af53-461a-b028-33ce9d1a9723_169809", "75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028", "9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97dc-b43dfad3d708_10087775", "fe23f7b6-56e1-4326-be6d-fe65b3ed0b89_513447477", "9d67d90b-c58f-4444-aaaa-88164c533333_281634985"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1082", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Several countries and companies are leading in the development of quantum computing, with significant investments and advancements being made in the field.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "China is currently leading in quantum computing research and development globally, with its Zuchongzhi No. 2 achieving record computing performance.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US is also a major player in the field, with companies like IBM and Google making significant advancements in quantum computing.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM is a leader in quantum systems development, with a focus on miniaturization and accuracy, and has delivered a 1,000-qubit quantum chip in 2023.", "citations": {"6e8266d8-b5ac-4c3a-a99c-09a11714a059_58364063": 1.0}}, {"text": "Canada is also a leader in quantum computing innovation, with investments of $40 million in Xanadu Quantum Technologies and $177.8 million in a quantum computing project.", "citations": {"9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97dc-b43dfad3d708_10087775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Canadian government has invested over $1 billion in quantum research, with the goal of becoming a global leader in quantum technology.", "citations": {"9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97dc-b43dfad3d708_10087775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Other countries, such as Germany, India, and Finland, are also investing heavily in quantum computing research and development.", "citations": {"e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158": 1.0, "fe23f7b6-56e1-4326-be6d-fe65b3ed0b89_513447477": 0.5, "b66d0211-a8df-41ef-ad2f-fe0bea54c328_288204630": 0.25}}, {"text": "The development of quantum computing has the potential to impact various fields, including communications, cryptography, and intelligence, and will require nations to address the ecosystem.", "citations": {"fe23f7b6-56e1-4326-be6d-fe65b3ed0b89_513447477": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers have the potential to solve complex computational problems beyond current computers, but error rates are still high in current quantum computing technology.", "citations": {"9c3176a9-1b4c-4b46-a54c-239b709436c3_419379195": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global quantum computing industry is expected to be worth $139 billion by 2045, with applications in drug development, material design, and energy.", "citations": {"9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97dc-b43dfad3d708_10087775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The University of Chicago and Tokyo have partnered on a quantum supercomputer, with the University of Chicago joining global quantum computing leadership.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM and Google have funded a $150 million quantum initiative, aiming to develop a 100,000 qubit quantum supercomputer.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0}}, {"text": "China has delivered its first practical quantum computer to a customer, a 24-qubit Wuyan system using superconducting technology.", "citations": {"9c3176a9-1b4c-4b46-a54c-239b709436c3_419379195": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM plans to deliver a 4,000-plus qubit machine by 2025, with a roadmap that includes the 133-qubit Heron processor in 2023 and the 462-qubit Flamingo processor in 2024.", "citations": {"1c816133-af53-461a-b028-33ce9d1a9723_169809": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google's Sycamore quantum processor has 70 qubits, more than its earlier version, and can make calculations in seconds that take classical computers 47 years.", "citations": {"94794363-e80c-409a-86b3-9050c7a2f74d_169695826": 1.0}}, {"text": "Jiuzhang 3.0 is 10 quadrillion times faster than supercomputers in GBS problems, using 255 detected photons for quantum computing.", "citations": {"b9642b3c-92cf-414d-955a-d55613c32464_1044927818": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM's Eagle quantum computer has 127 qubits, making it the fastest quantum processor, and it exceeds traditional computer processing power.", "citations": {"624d0d4a-3bf6-442e-9929-d3eed9c51685_633237259": 1.0}}, {"text": "The development of quantum computing is a global effort, with countries like the US, China, Japan, and Europe investing heavily in research and development.", "citations": {"9770a613-f6c5-439d-9196-e287506e3e26_404039217": 1.0, "a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 0.5, "f6185e03-eec8-473d-9de9-2cbc823d416c_155400207": 0.25}}, {"text": "The key opportunities in integrating quantum computing with classical systems include the potential for massive increases in processing power, improvements in energy efficiency, and the ability to solve complex problems that are impossible for conventional supercomputers.", "citations": {"9770a613-f6c5-439d-9196-e287506e3e26_404039217": 1.0, "d816a976-8bc4-4328-9818-89a6a7f645ae_914613889": 0.5}}, {"text": "However, there are also significant challenges to be addressed, including the need for better interchip communications, the development of robust error correction methods, and the integration of quantum and classical computing systems.", "citations": {"1c816133-af53-461a-b028-33ce9d1a9723_169809": 1.0, "a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 0.5, "b32bb298-210c-43d8-8b00-fde663665b52_860518335": 0.25}}, {"text": "Quantum error correction is crucial for practical quantum computers, and companies like IBM and Google are making significant breakthroughs in this area.", "citations": {"765f6998-50e6-42d0-b3c8-ed3d39896f44_511622726": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM has reduced the number of qubits required for error correction by a factor of 10, which is a major milestone in the development of scalable quantum systems.", "citations": {"4d5e6fac-834b-4526-a7c1-a5be27446277_703470420": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google has achieved a quantum computing breakthrough with fewer errors, and their new algorithms have increased the qubit array dimension while lowering the error rate.", "citations": {"e46ecccd-fed2-4d87-b426-e8abb60748cc_682028010": 1.0}}, {"text": "The development of quantum error correction techniques, such as quantum error correction codes and error mitigation strategies, is essential for the scalability and reliability of quantum computing systems.", "citations": {"01172bcc-2f72-41ea-99ae-1b09283b41da_328555448": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing systems have the potential to solve important problems, such as simulating molecules, which has applications for energy efficiency and medicine.", "citations": {"7651b719-37d8-43eb-993c-c01d94f09705_226848253": 1.0}}, {"text": "Countries and companies are investing heavily in quantum computing, with an estimated 30-300 million physical qubits needed to break Bitcoin encryption.", "citations": {"7651b719-37d8-43eb-993c-c01d94f09705_226848253": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Honghai Research Institute is sharing research with the Taiwan Quantum Team, and researchers have demonstrated a new way to represent logical qubits with hardware stability.", "citations": {"295849d0-cebc-4cbc-9082-a7fe57edba2a_854692893": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum error correction reduces hardware error rate and is crucial for long-distance communication, with quantum repeaters using quantum memories for long-distance communication.", "citations": {"3117a9e4-b3c0-4d0d-bb9d-b9f4c91e3eeb_52405326": 1.0}}, {"text": "Machine learning methods can improve error correction outcome and longer distance communication, with reinforcement learning agents optimizing the error correction process.", "citations": {"a50e520c-6ba4-445c-ba2a-565b4a0794e4_368273242": 1.0}}, {"text": "In conclusion, the development of quantum computing is a rapidly advancing field, with significant investments and advancements being made by countries and companies around the world.", "citations": {"4adef761-07af-492c-b519-7fb1ceac5dad_416845054": 1.0, "75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 0.5, "6e8266d8-b5ac-4c3a-a99c-09a11714a059_58364063": 0.25, "9e5a561a-235a-4cee-97d