{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1083", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Woolly mammoths went extinct due to human hunting and climate change.", "citations": {"0e0119f8-d14f-4a45-ab93-aad438f4974a_761313705": 1.0}}, {"text": "The woolly mammoths are believed to have gone extinct between 10,000 to 50,000 years ago, possibly due to climate change altering vegetation around 13,000 years ago.", "citations": {"254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human-induced climate change, including a 5.5 degree Celsius temperature rise, contributed to wildfires and the extinction of woolly mammoths.", "citations": {"254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187": 1.0}}, {"text": "Genetic analysis revealed the mammoth's life history, providing insights into the impact of early human migration on woolly mammoth populations.", "citations": {"801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983": 1.0}}, {"text": "The mammoth's death coincided with early human inhabitants, with isotope analysis revealing their complex interactions through migration patterns and diet.", "citations": {"801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983": 1.0}}, {"text": "Woolly mammoths on Wrangel Island survived for 6,000 years after mainland extinction, disappearing 4,000 years ago due to possible disease, fire, or climate factors.", "citations": {"8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mammoths died out due to sharp climate change that replaced their pastures with trees and swamp plants, making it hard for them to find food.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "Woolly mammoths were hunted by Stone Age people and likely driven to extinction around 4,000 years ago.", "citations": {"bb5ee390-e6fd-4ccd-b986-4f710b861f4d_74980133": 1.0}}, {"text": "Hunting methods for woolly mammoths varied, with evidence of spearpoints and stone tools found in Nebraska dating back to the Clovis culture.", "citations": {"fa330bff-4d70-4a82-9ef5-39d0a9c33a63_1008639065": 1.0}}, {"text": "The discovery of mammoth bones in Austria suggests that humans may have set traps, indicating coordination and planning.", "citations": {"0e0119f8-d14f-4a45-ab93-aad438f4974a_761313705": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths was likely caused by a combination of climate change, human hunting, and loss of genetic diversity.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "Studying woolly mammoth extinction informs our understanding of climate change and human impacts on modern ecosystems.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths resulted from multiple factors, including climate change and human hunting, and understanding these interactions is crucial for preserving biodiversity.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}], "references": ["254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187", "8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249", "fa330bff-4d70-4a82-9ef5-39d0a9c33a63_1008639065", "0e0119f8-d14f-4a45-ab93-aad438f4974a_761313705", "074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440", "801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983", "bb5ee390-e6fd-4ccd-b986-4f710b861f4d_74980133", "f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426", "be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1084", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The woolly mammoths went extinct around 10,000 years ago, with the exact cause of their extinction still debated among researchers.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}, {"text": "The primary factors that contributed to the extinction of woolly mammoths include climate change, which reduced their habitats and made them vulnerable to other threats.", "citations": {"44424d28-dcbb-4e8d-b7d3-46eee5796966_522924419": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human hunting is also believed to have played a role in the decline of woolly mammoth populations, with evidence suggesting that humans interacted with mammoths in Siberia for 800 years.", "citations": {"d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change led to a reduction in the availability of food for mammoths, making it difficult for them to survive, and the warming climate caused the replacement of former mammoth pastures with trees and swamp plants.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "The loss of genetic diversity in woolly mammoths, due to limited mutations, small population sizes, and inbreeding, also affected their ability to adapt to changing environments, making them more vulnerable to extinction.", "citations": {"2fe013ba-6461-48b8-9d91-d5e1f303874a_358135628": 1.0}}, {"text": "The isolation of mammoth populations, such as those on Wrangel Island, contributed to their low genetic diversity, making them more susceptible to extinction.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths had a significant impact on the ecosystem, leading to an increase in grassland fires and a change in the composition of plant species.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study of woolly mammoth genetics has provided valuable insights into their evolution, adaptation, and extinction, with researchers analyzing DNA from fossils and excrement to reconstruct their genetic history.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The comparison of woolly mammoth genomes to elephant genomes has also provided insights into their evolutionary history, with millions of base pairs differing between the two species.", "citations": {"0a81051f-2d25-4a93-9ec6-b902eb792647_997407507": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the extinction of woolly mammoths was likely the result of a combination of factors, including climate change, human hunting, and the loss of genetic diversity, with further research needed to fully understand the complex interactions that led to their demise.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "The temporal correlation between climate change, human hunting, and the decline of woolly mammoths suggests that the factors interacted to contribute to their extinction over a period of thousands of years.", "citations": {"90c8561c-8bd6-4cdc-8d7c-226981ff7db9_703546247": 1.0}}, {"text": "The spatial correlation between climate change, human hunting, and the decline of woolly mammoths shows that the factors affected different regions and populations, including the Wrangel Island population, which survived for 6,000 years after the mainland extinction.", "citations": {"7ae40e2b-8a33-4be4-8307-c3c08a1eb04b_761501946": 1.0}}, {"text": "The decline of woolly mammoths was a gradual process that occurred over thousands of years, with the population dwindling due to climate change, human hunting, and other factors.", "citations": {"801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983": 1.0}}, {"text": "The exact cause of the woolly mammoths' disappearance remains unknown, but it is assumed to be a sudden event, possibly a disease outbreak or climatic perturbation.", "citations": {"8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study of the woolly mammoths' extinction provides valuable insights into the impacts of climate change and human activity on ecosystems and the importance of conservation efforts to protect vulnerable species.", "citations": {"c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 1.0}}, {"text": "The analysis of mammoth remains and fossils has revealed that human hunting may have had a significant impact on woolly mammoth populations, particularly in certain regions and time periods.", "citations": {"801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983": 1.0}}, {"text": "The discovery of a 17,000-year-old mammoth fossil in Alaska, with a well-preserved tusk, has provided new insights into the life and death of these magnificent creatures.", "citations": {"13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130": 1.0}}, {"text": "The estimated impact of human hunting on woolly mammoth populations is still a topic of ongoing research and debate, with new findings and discoveries shedding more light on the complex relationships between humans and animals in the past.", "citations": {"0e0119f8-d14f-4a45-ab93-aad438f4974a_761313705": 1.0}}, {"text": "The loss of megafauna, including woolly mammoths, increased grassland fires 50,000 years ago, and wildfire activity increased after megafauna extinction.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths is believed to have occurred around 4,000 years ago, with the last surviving mammoths found on Wrangel Island.", "citations": {"90c8561c-8bd6-4cdc-8d7c-226981ff7db9_703546247": 1.0}}, {"text": "The island mammoth population had low genetic diversity due to interbreeding, but inbreeding was not the primary cause of their extinction.", "citations": {"90c8561c-8bd6-4cdc-8d7c-226981ff7db9_703546247": 1.0}}, {"text": "A random event, rather than genetics, is believed to have caused the extinction of the Wrangel Island mammoths.", "citations": {"90c8561c-8bd6-4cdc-8d7c-226981ff7db9_703546247": 1.0}}, {"text": "The genetic diversity of the Wrangel Island mammoths was low due to inbreeding, but it is not thought to have been fatal.", "citations": {"8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249": 1.0}}, {"text": "The population of mammoths on Wrangel Island grew from 8 to 300 individuals over 20 generations, but eventually declined and became extinct.", "citations": {"8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249": 1.0}}, {"text": "The loss of genetic diversity and the isolation of mammoth populations made them more susceptible to disease outbreaks and the introduction of new species, which may have contributed to their decline.", "citations": {"c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 1.0}}, {"text": "Natural selection purged harmful variants in the mammoth population, but genetic drift preserved mutations across generations in small populations.", "citations": {"c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths had a significant impact on the ecosystem, leading to an increase in grassland fires and a change in the composition of plant species.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "The collapse of mammoth populations also had a ripple effect on the food chain, leading to the decline of predators and fruit trees that relied on them for seed dispersal.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "The reduction of food supply due to climate change was a major contributor to the extinction of woolly mammoths.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "The mammoths were unable to adapt quickly enough to the changes in their landscape, which ultimately led to their extinction.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human activity, including hunting and habitat destruction, may have contributed to the extinction of woolly mammoths, but the primary cause is still debated among researchers.", "citations": {"254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187": 1.0}}, {"text": "The analysis of DNA from mammoth remains has provided valuable insights into the causes of their extinction, including the effects of climate change and genetic diversity.", "citations": {"c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study of mammoth migration patterns and habitat use has also shed light on the spatial correlation between climate change and mammoth extinction.", "citations": {"13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130": 1.0}}, {"text": "The temporal correlation between human hunting and mammoth extinction is supported by the discovery of mammoth remains with evidence of human hunting, such as spear wounds.", "citations": {"801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983": 1.0}}, {"text": "The interaction between climate change and human hunting is complex, and further research is needed to fully understand the causes of woolly mammoth extinction.", "citations": {"d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018": 1.0}}, {"text": "The decline of mammoth populations was likely a gradual process, with climate change and human hunting contributing to a decline in population size and genetic diversity over time.", "citations": {"7ae40e2b-8a33-4be4-8307-c3c08a1eb04b_761501946": 1.0}}, {"text": "The exact cause of woolly mammoth extinction remains unknown, but it is clear that climate change and human activity played significant roles in their decline.", "citations": {"8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study of woolly mammoth extinction can provide valuable lessons for conservation efforts, highlighting the importance of preserving genetic diversity and protecting habitats from human impact.", "citations": {"c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 1.0}}, {"text": "The correlation between climate change and mammoth extinction is supported by the fact that mammoths survived several ice ages without significant impact, but were unable to adapt to the rapid climate change that occurred at the end of the last ice age.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The woolly mammoths were well adapted to the cold climates of the Pleistocene era, but were ultimately unable to adapt to the rapid environmental changes that occurred at the end of the last ice age.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths and other megafauna has had a lasting impact on the environment, including a reduction in nutrient movement and a change in the composition of plant species.", "citations": {"6e875fd5-8b9f-4a3c-89e3-c522ed5d041d_983323011": 1.0}}, {"text": "The causes of the woolly mammoth's extinction are complex and multifaceted, and likely included a combination of factors, including climate change, human hunting, and other environmental factors.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}], "references": ["be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929", "c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691", "44424d28-dcbb-4e8d-b7d3-46eee5796966_522924419", "d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613", "f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426", "2fe013ba-6461-48b8-9d91-d5e1f303874a_358135628", "0a81051f-2d25-4a93-9ec6-b902eb792647_997407507", "8b7ae3bf-7e10-4da9-acb0-af164180ff42_548743249", "13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130", "254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187", "6e875fd5-8b9f-4a3c-89e3-c522ed5d041d_983323011", "0e0119f8-d14f-4a45-ab93-aad438f4974a_761313705", "801b918b-354c-4167-9a6e-d3421874103f_716155983", "d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018", "074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440", "90c8561c-8bd6-4cdc-8d7c-226981ff7db9_703546247", "7ae40e2b-8a33-4be4-8307-c3c08a1eb04b_761501946"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1085", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Greenland is rich in rare-earth minerals, including neodymium and praseodymium, found in South Greenland.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country has a favourable legal framework for mining, with a supportive government and robust infrastructure.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0}}, {"text": "Companies like AEX Gold, NEO, and Kobold Metals are interested in extracting rare earth minerals and metals from Greenland.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0, "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 0.5, "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 0.25}}, {"text": "The Tanbreez mine in Greenland is expected to start rare earth production in 2024, with 19 million tons of rare earth oxides, including 30% heavy elements.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Guanast deposit in Greenland holds the world's second-largest rare earth reserves.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU has signed a strategic partnership with Greenland on sustainable raw materials.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland has 25 of the EU's 34 critical raw materials.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extracting rare earth minerals in Greenland poses logistical and infrastructure challenges, including costly separation processes.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland has banned uranium mining and halted rare earth deposit development in the south.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Investors like Bill Gates and Bezos, and companies such as Kobold Metals and NEO, are investing in Greenland's mineral development, including nickel, cobalt, and rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0, "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 0.5}}, {"text": "Investing in rare earth mineral extraction in Greenland poses environmental, health, and regulatory risks.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Possible deposits are primarily found in South Greenland, notably at the Surftog Carbonatite complex and the Tanbreez mine.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0, "95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 0.5}}, {"text": "Extraction ease varies by location and mineral type, with some, like the Tanbreez mine, requiring costly factory separation.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Countries and companies like AEX Gold, NEO, Kobold Metals, the EU, and China's Shenghe Resources are interested in extracting these minerals.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0, "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 0.5, "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 0.25, "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 0.125}}], "references": ["95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580", "4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299", "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406", "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907", "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436", "791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498", "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1086", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "Greenland has significant rare earth deposits, including the world's second-largest reserves, accounting for 10% of global production.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country has an estimated 16.2 million tons of unexploited rare earth minerals in mineral sands deposits worldwide.", "citations": {"68a49fb2-1e39-4c5e-95fc-4fa32a640b82_624223814": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rare earth deposits have been found in Greenland, including the Kuannersuit and Kvanefjeld areas.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extracting rare earth minerals in Greenland is expected to be challenging due to environmental concerns.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "AEX Gold plans to mine high-grade gold in South Greenland using renewable energy.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0}}, {"text": "The company plans to use existing infrastructure and local renewable energy to power its mining operations.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tanbreez Mining plans to mine 19 million tons of rare earth oxides in Greenland.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The European Union has signed a strategic partnership with Greenland to develop sustainable raw material value chains, including rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The partnership aims to ensure environmentally responsible rare earth mineral extraction in Greenland with high ESG standards.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "China is interested in developing rare earth mining in Greenland, with companies like Shenghe Resources having subsidiaries there.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Greenlandic government has banned uranium mining to prevent large-scale rare earth expansion.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Billionaires like Bezos, Gates, and Bloomberg are funding mineral searches in Greenland, including rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland may have large deposits of nickel, cobalt, coal, copper, gold, and rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "KoBold Metals is searching for rare earth minerals in Greenland's Disko-Nuussuaq project with a $15 million budget through 2024.", "citations": {"fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Disko project has potential for copper, nickel, cobalt, and lithium deposits, key minerals for EV batteries.", "citations": {"fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Arctic region's mineral resources, including Greenland, are valued at over $30 trillion, mostly from energy resources.", "citations": {"3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021": 1.0}}, {"text": "Developing Arctic projects requires huge investments, hindering Greenland's rare earth mineral extraction.", "citations": {"3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021": 1.0}}, {"text": "China and Russia are among countries investing in Arctic mineral resources.", "citations": {"3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021": 1.0}}, {"text": "Global demand for rare earth minerals is expected to rise sixfold by 2030, driven by the green transition.", "citations": {"1386537b-bf3d-4315-a007-8aa02221c0b3_529952141": 1.0}}, {"text": "The increasing demand may lead to further interest in Greenland's rare earth deposits.", "citations": {"1386537b-bf3d-4315-a007-8aa02221c0b3_529952141": 1.0}}, {"text": "The European Union aims to meet 10% of its rare earth demand by 2030, possibly by developing Arctic sources.", "citations": {"55b8be09-9e6d-40d3-9d0d-8f5f641072d1_884532803": 1.0}}, {"text": "China dominates the global rare earth market, accounting for 70% of mining and 90% of magnet processing.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU and other countries may seek alternative rare earth sources, including Arctic ones, to reduce reliance on Chinese imports.", "citations": {"55b8be09-9e6d-40d3-9d0d-8f5f641072d1_884532803": 1.0}}, {"text": "Possible deposits in Greenland include the Tanbreez mine and the Disko project, where KoBold Metals owns 49%.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0, "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 0.5}}, {"text": "Developing infrastructure and using AI are expected to facilitate the extraction of electric vehicle raw materials.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0, "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 0.5}}, {"text": "Greenland has the world's second-largest rare earth reserves.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country's rare earth minerals are crucial for electric vehicles and wind turbines.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extraction of rare earth minerals in Greenland harms the environment, prompting companies to seek reduction methods, including building separation factories.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU plans to diversify its rare earth supply chain by exploring alternative sources and technologies.", "citations": {"68a49fb2-1e39-4c5e-95fc-4fa32a640b82_624223814": 1.0}}, {"text": "NEO has a Greenland exploration license for rare earth metals and plans an Estonian magnet plant.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0}}, {"text": "The company aims to reduce its exposure to crude price volatility and diversify its rare earth ore sources.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extraction of rare earth minerals in Greenland faces environmental challenges due to climate change.", "citations": {"02e0cc0e-6a99-4de7-92b7-45909fe1b7f5_1034133963": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Greenland government has banned uranium mining, halting the Kuannersuit rare earth deposit's development.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country has signed an EU partnership for sustainable raw material development and high ESG standards.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Companies like KoBold Metals and Bluejay are investing in Greenland's mineral sector, which has emerging investment potential.", "citations": {"fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 1.0}}, {"text": "Denmark and Greenland have potential mineral hotspots that could lead to further rare earth development.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "Bill Gates, Michael Bloomberg, and Jeff Bezos are funding mineral searches in Greenland to diversify its economy.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's ice-free land is being assessed for potential large-scale mineral extraction.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country has the world's second-largest rare earth reserves, with the Guanast mine producing 10% of the global total.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extraction of rare earth minerals in Greenland faces significant obstacles due to environmental concerns and regulatory hurdles.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU and Greenland have signed a strategic partnership on raw materials to promote sustainability and high governance standards.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The partnership focuses on sustainable mineral resource exploitation through infrastructure, capacity, and skills development.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland has revoked a Chinese mining license and banned uranium mining.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has banned uranium deposit exploration after the Inuit Ataqatigiit party won an election on an environmental platform.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "New prime minister Mute Egede opposes the Guanast Rare Earth Mine, the world's second-largest rare earth reserve.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Sungho Resources has acquired a 12.5% stake in Greenland Minerals.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Greenland government regulates the rare earth sector to ensure responsible operations.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country's mineral sector is expected to drive sustainable economic growth.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government prioritizes high environmental and social governance standards in the rare earth mineral sector.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU and Greenland cooperate to develop the rare earth mineral sector.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland is eligible for EU funding for research on rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government provides Earth observation data to facilitate rare earth mineral development.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government regulates mining licenses, including rare earth mineral extraction.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland revoked a Chinese company's mining license, enforcing regulations in the rare earth sector.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland is rich in minerals, including iron ore and rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government banned uranium mining, impacting the rare earth mineral sector.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland has rare earth mines, such as Kuannersuit, operated by licensed companies.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government offers licenses to companies, including those extracting rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "Companies in Greenland must pay guarantees to ensure responsible mining operations.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government demands the cleanup of abandoned mines to protect the environment and local communities.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland requires the return of geological data to inform future rare earth mineral development.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government issues mining licenses for rare earths, including the Tanbreez Mining project.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tanbreez Mining is expected to start production in 2024, establishing Greenland as a significant rare earth minerals producer.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The mine contains 19 million tons of rare earth oxides, one of the world's largest deposits.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The mine contains 30% heavy rare earth elements, crucial for certain technologies.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's rare earths are used in electric vehicles and wind turbines, a critical part of the renewable energy sector.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The mine holds over half of the world's rare earth resources.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "A factory with significant investment and equipment is needed to separate rare earths from rocks.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Separating rare earths requires $40 million in equipment, highlighting the sector's significant development costs.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU plans to diversify its rare earth supply chain by increasing domestic production.", "citations": {}}], "references": ["55b8be09-9e6d-40d3-9d0d-8f5f641072d1_884532803", "1386537b-bf3d-4315-a007-8aa02221c0b3_529952141", "3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021", "4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299", "68a49fb2-1e39-4c5e-95fc-4fa32a640b82_624223814", "95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580", "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406", "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089", "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436", "02e0cc0e-6a99-4de7-92b7-45909fe1b7f5_1034133963", "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907", "791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498", "841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1087", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The India-Russia relationship has deepened under Modi and Putin, with cooperation in defense, energy, and trade.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have a Special and Privileged Strategic Partnership strengthened under Prime Minister Modi and President Putin's leadership.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries have signed 28 agreements and set targets of $50 billion in investment and $30 billion in trade by 2025.", "citations": {"21ed01ca-807c-44ff-a30d-2f665ef65e50_383211104": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has resisted US pressure to condemn Russia over Ukraine, instead maintaining its strategic partnership and buying discounted Russian oil.", "citations": {"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia cooperate in the military-technical sphere, jointly producing the BrahMos cruise missile and AK-203 rifles.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US has warned India of sanctions over the Russian S-400 purchase, but India continues to cooperate with Russia on military equipment despite Western pressure.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have discussed joint production of modern weapons and signed a 10-year military cooperation agreement to strengthen bilateral ties.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_919335038": 1.0}}, {"text": "India's rivalry with China has influenced its relationship with Russia, with India increasing Russian oil purchases 20-fold since 2021 to counter Putin's potential closeness to China.", "citations": {"8fa58a36-330a-43f1-b8b1-1b3ec51f7ad8_406552592": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia supports India's UN Security Council bid and they cooperate through BRICS.", "citations": {"fb598f31-8502-4e92-9ac3-16b6d05569c7_495735171": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship will likely continue to evolve, balancing interests with countries like the US and China, and remain key to regional security.", "citations": {"5e5bc85c-68f7-4bdc-943d-afe175b3dc6f_946376914": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship has significant implications for regional security, as India counters Chinese aggression and Russia strengthens ties with both nations.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}], "references": ["362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628", "d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_919335038", "fb598f31-8502-4e92-9ac3-16b6d05569c7_495735171", "18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163", "21ed01ca-807c-44ff-a30d-2f665ef65e50_383211104", "5e5bc85c-68f7-4bdc-943d-afe175b3dc6f_946376914", "9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430", "d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719", "8fa58a36-330a-43f1-b8b1-1b3ec51f7ad8_406552592"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "still", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1088", "run_id": "still-proposed"}, "responses": [{"text": "The India-Russia relationship has strengthened under Modi and Putin, focusing on defense and trade.", "citations": {"21ed01ca-807c-44ff-a30d-2f665ef65e50_383211104": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia is India's largest arms supplier and a key defense partner.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has maintained strong ties with Russia, calling for an end to Ukraine hostilities without criticizing Russia.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship is vital for regional security, with the Indian Foreign Minister visiting Moscow to discuss issues amid the Ukraine conflict.", "citations": {"5d2aa3ea-03e3-4be1-9776-22b48d27873b_405058174": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia seeks to maintain a special relationship with India, its main arms buyer, which hasn't condemned the Ukraine invasion.", "citations": {"5d2aa3ea-03e3-4be1-9776-22b48d27873b_405058174": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia's ties with China have driven a wedge between India and Russia.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "India remains dependent on Russia for most of its military equipment.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US has threatened India with sanctions over its purchase of Russia's S-400 missile system.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia has offered India the S-500 missile system and jointly produced the BrahMos cruise missile system with them.", "citations": {"18a87794-ba47-4d33-a1b5-bf97307dd44b_224507163": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two leaders aim for $50 billion in bilateral investment and $30 billion in trade by 2025.", "citations": {"21ed01ca-807c-44ff-a30d-2f665ef65e50_383211104": 1.0}}, {"text": "Trade between India and Russia has risen by 60 percent, driven mainly by Indian imports of Russian oil and fertilizers.", "citations": {"4ff724c6-0122-4a1b-adf0-e28d967863c7_882892101": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has resisted US pressure over Ukraine, instead buying discounted Russian oil and making Russia its largest supplier.", "citations": {"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries will expand cooperation in the Russian Far East, including joint production of modern weapons.", "citations": {"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430": 1.0}}, {"text": "Putin has praised Modi's stance on national interests and invited him to visit Russia in 2024.", "citations": {"9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship has been impacted by the Quad, a group formed to counter China.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries have a \"special and privileged strategic partnership\" with a 10-year military cooperation agreement.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have extended their military-technical cooperation to 2031 and signed an oil agreement.", "citations": {"d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_919335038": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries have a \"special strategic partnership\" and cooperated during the COVID-19 crisis.", "citations": {"d749981a-0acd-425d-8652-51e8701d6755_959152834": 1.0}}, {"text": "Putin has praised Modi and awarded him the Order of St. Andrew.", "citations": {"deba499a-e703-48ed-9cfa-527c88177b1c_305764772": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries have a privileged strategic partnership, supporting large joint trade and economic projects.", "citations": {"deba499a-e703-48ed-9cfa-527c88177b1c_305764772": 1.0}}, {"text": "The partnership has advanced in several areas and the two countries are part of the BRICS association.", "citations": {"e98fd00f-f920-48f3-856b-60417d5ac5a9_698643939": 1.0}}, {"text": "PM Modi visited Russia to review ties with Putin and discuss bilateral relations.", "citations": {"e98fd00f-f920-48f3-856b-60417d5ac5a9_698643939": 1.0}}, {"text": "The two countries aim for a peaceful and stable region and have cooperation in health, education, and culture.", "citations": {"e98fd00f-f920-48f3-856b-60417d5ac5a9_698643939": 1.0}}, {"text": "India relies on Russia for 90% of its military equipment, crucial for its national security.", "citations": {"9afa62f4-4578-4ea7-a91a-72772c5ad986_226877513": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US has concerns about India's Russia ties and Ukraine stance.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India is balancing relationships with the US, Russia, and China while diversifying defense purchases from countries like Israel, the US, and France.", "citations": {"a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have historical ties, with Russia being India's largest arms supplier.", "citations": {"a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382": 1.0}}, {"text": "India buys $60 billion worth of Russian goods, including large amounts of oil, annually.", "citations": {"a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia's trade has risen from $15 billion to $65 billion and is targeted to reach $100 billion by 2030.", "citations": {"af9ac9a2-6de8-4c50-8380-cdfe8381ce2a_864187021": 1.0}}, {"text": "India considers Russia a long-term partner and friend, despite growing US ties.", "citations": {"af9ac9a2-6de8-4c50-8380-cdfe8381ce2a_864187021": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship impacts regional security in South Asia, amid the Ukraine conflict and India-China tensions.", "citations": {"5d2aa3ea-03e3-4be1-9776-22b48d27873b_405058174": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia's ties with China may pressure Moscow to downgrade its ties with India.", "citations": {"766de50a-6bd4-4890-bf69-2ed01a941693_299514041": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia has helped defuse India-China tensions in the past, and the two countries have had a strategic partnership since 2000.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have discussed the Ukraine crisis and agreed on the importance of regional peace and stability.", "citations": {"5d2aa3ea-03e3-4be1-9776-22b48d27873b_405058174": 1.0}}, {"text": "The India-Russia relationship is expected to continue evolving as they strengthen economic and strategic ties amidst a complex geopolitical landscape.", "citations": {"af9ac9a2-6de8-4c50-8380-cdfe8381ce2a_864187021": 1.0}}, {"text": "India values Russia as a partner in economy and security, particularly in balancing relations with China.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia and India's bilateral trade reached $65 billion in 2023-2024.", "citations": {"af9ac9a2-6de8-4c50-8380-cdfe8381ce2a_864187021": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has resisted US pressure and increased Russian oil purchases despite the Ukraine invasion.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia's isolation may push Putin closer to China, impacting India's regional security.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia will jointly produce military equipment and collaborate on the Kudankulam nuclear project, strengthening their strategic partnership.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "India aims to strengthen military ties with Russia to counterbalance China's growing influence.", "citations": {"05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia will support India against China as part of their mutual respect-based relationship.", "citations": {"343c3418-0c85-417f-9de1-d9118753f7ee_616934410": 1.0}}, {"text": "India wants Russia to remain a global power to counterbalance China's dominance.", "citations": {"343c3418-0c85-417f-9de1-d9118753f7ee_616934410": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US views India as a key ally to counter China, affecting India-Russia ties.", "citations": {"343c3418-0c85-417f-9de1-d9118753f7ee_616934410": 1.0}}, {"text": "China supports Russia over Ukraine, highlighting their growing cooperation.", "citations": {"343c3418-0c85-417f-9de1-d9118753f7ee_616934410": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have a long-standing diplomatic relationship, with Russia's strength weakening due to Western sanctions.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia relies on China, impacting its relationship with India.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "India relies on Russia for its military needs.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia supports India on issues like Kashmir, reflecting their strategic cooperation.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "China and Russia have a \"no limits\" partnership, impacting India-Russia ties and regional dynamics.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Ukraine war has eroded Russia's electronics production, potentially impacting its India ties.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia's weakness increases its reliance on China, impacting its relationship with India.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "India needs a strong Russia relationship due to Chinese aggression.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "China killed 20 Indian soldiers in June 2020, heightening India-China tensions.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628": 1.0}}, {"text": "India reconsiders its China ties, affecting its Russia relationship.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "China's promotion of a multipolar world does not extend to accommodating India's interests.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India's alignment with the US and allies may impact its relationship with Russia due to China.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and China had a rapprochement in the late 1970s during the Cold War.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and China signed confidence-building measures to improve their relationship.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India seeks a strong Russia relationship to counter China's economic and military might.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "China's actions along disputed border regions with India have heightened tensions.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India's military policy now includes the Quad and Indo-Pacific Strategy, affecting its relationship with Russia.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India is shifting its focus to Southeast Asia for connectivity projects to diversify regional relationships.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India supports a rules-based order in the Indo-Pacific region.", "citations": {"362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514": 1.0}}, {"text": "India relies on Russian technology for its military hardware.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia supports India in the UN and multilateral organizations.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India signed a $5.43 billion deal with Russia for the S-400 missile system.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia is a key partner for India's defence manufacturing programs.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has reduced its Russian military hardware imports from 65% to 49% to diversify its defence relationships.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US may waive CAATSA for India's S-400 deal due to shared China concerns.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia names India as a key partner in its Military Strategy document.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India and Russia have had a Strategic Partnership since 2000.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia has not delayed hardware support to India during the China standoff.", "citations": {"76ea5cd5-b2de-4145-a40b-be0ab18fa95c_99407596": 1.0}}, {"text": "India purchased $3.4 billion in US military equipment in 2020, highlighting its efforts to diversify relationships.", "citations": {}}], "references": ["343c3418-0c85-417f-9de1-d9118753f7ee_616934410", "9796598e-e5cd-4b19-8665-f50cecfea01d_371231430", "d749981a-0acd-425d-8652-51e8701d6755_959152834", "21ed01ca-807c-44ff-a30d-2f665ef65e50_383211104", "d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_919335038", "af9ac9a2-6de8-4c50-8380-cdfe8381ce2a_864187021", "d67e54cc-62da-447c-ae1b-48796fdb0f91_766762719", "362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_301706628", "e98fd00f-f920-48f3-856b-60417d5ac5a9_698643939", "4ff724c6-0122-4a1b-adf0-e28d967863c7_882892101", "05ddbc47-8544-4bb7-8449-143ff74e846a_947839176", "5d2aa3ea-03e3-4be1-9776-22b48d27873b_405058174", "9afa62f4-4578-4ea7-a91a-72772c5ad986_226877513", "362c2c86-f85e-4fb2-a284-cd4f44e4aee0_753771514", "deba499a-e703-48ed-9cfa-527c88177b1c_305764772", "a8edad1b-d157-466a-9ba5-057e6b4399d9_841501382", "76ea5cd5-b2d